[ceiling fan thrumming]

03:57.487 --> 04:00.866
[Helicopter approaches]

04:16.798 --> 04:17.758
[Willard] Saigon.

04:19.885 --> 04:20.969
Shit.

04:22.971 --> 04:24.681
I'm still only in Saigon.

04:33.482 --> 04:36.818
Every time, I think I'm going to wake up
back in the jungle.

04:43.074 --> 04:45.911
When I was home after my first tour,
it was worse.

04:55.045 --> 04:56.713
I'd wake up, and there'd be nothing.

05:05.514 --> 05:07.307
I hardly said a word to my wife,

05:07.432 --> 05:09.184
until I said yes to a divorce.

05:12.771 --> 05:14.815
When I was here, I wanted to be there.

05:16.316 --> 05:17.651
When I was there,

05:18.068 --> 05:20.529
all I could think of
was getting back into the jungle.

05:24.574 --> 05:25.784
I'm here a week now...

05:29.996 --> 05:31.248
waiting for a mission...

05:33.083 --> 05:34.125
getting softer.

05:40.090 --> 05:42.467
Every minute I stay in this room,
I get weaker.

05:43.593 --> 05:46.721
And every minute Charlie squats
in the bush, he gets stronger.

05:52.477 --> 05:53.979
Each time I looked around,

05:54.062 --> 05:56.022
the walls moved in a little tighter.

