♪ Yeah ♪

07:06.718 --> 07:07.594
♪ Yeah ♪

07:08.678 --> 07:10.138
♪ Yeah ♪

07:36.164 --> 07:38.124
[Willard] Everyone gets
everything he wants.

07:39.793 --> 07:41.127
I wanted a mission...

07:42.504 --> 07:44.297
and for my sins, they gave me one.

07:46.424 --> 07:48.134
Brought it up to me like room service.

07:48.218 --> 07:49.094
[knocking on the door]

07:49.594 --> 07:51.262
[soldier] Captain Willard,
are you in there?

07:52.681 --> 07:53.974
[Willard] Yeah, I'm coming.

07:54.933 --> 07:56.726
It was a real choice mission,

07:57.978 --> 07:59.145
and when it was over...

08:00.563 --> 08:01.731
I'd never want another.

08:01.982 --> 08:06.027
[locks clicking]

08:10.407 --> 08:11.282
What do you want?

08:11.825 --> 08:12.867
Are you all right, Captain?

08:13.034 --> 08:13.910
What's it look like?

08:24.129 --> 08:26.589
[soldier] Are you Captain Willard,
505th Battalion?

08:26.715 --> 08:28.174
-[Willard] Affirmative.
-[soldier] 173rd Airborne...

08:28.258 --> 08:29.509
-Yep.
-...assigned to Salk?

08:29.592 --> 08:31.344
Hey, buddy, are you gonna shut the door?

08:33.513 --> 08:34.389
[door closes]

08:34.472 --> 08:36.558
[soldier] We have orders
to escort you to the airfield.

08:39.894 --> 08:40.979
What are the charges?

08:41.146 --> 08:42.063
[soldier] Sir?

08:42.230 --> 08:43.231
What did I do?

08:43.565 --> 08:45.025
There's no charges, Captain.

08:45.316 --> 08:48.778
You have orders to report to COMSEC
intelligence at Nha Trang.

08:50.363 --> 08:51.239
I see.

08:51.406 --> 08:52.282
[soldier] All right?

08:52.407 --> 08:53.491
Nha Trang for me.

08:53.616 --> 08:54.534
[soldier] That's right.

08:55.827 --> 08:58.288
Come on, Captain, you still have
a few hours to get cleaned up.

08:58.663 --> 09:00.081
[Willard] I'm not feeling too good.

09:00.623 --> 09:01.541
[soldier] Captain?

09:03.418 --> 09:05.837
Dave, come here and give me a hand.
We got a dead one.

09:06.296 --> 09:08.256
Come on, Captain. Let's take a shower.

09:08.465 --> 09:09.758
Ah, don't be an ass.

09:10.008 --> 09:12.218
[soldier] Get a hold of him. We're going
to take a shower, Captain.

09:12.343 --> 09:13.511
Come on, in we go.

09:13.636 --> 09:15.263
[Dave] Now, stand underneath this,
Captain.

09:15.472 --> 09:16.556
[screams]

09:17.140 --> 09:18.224
Oh!

09:18.600 --> 09:22.145
[helicopter whirs]

09:27.609 --> 09:29.778
[Willard] I was going to the worst place
in the world,

09:29.861 --> 09:31.154
and I didn't even know it yet.

09:33.198 --> 09:37.035
Weeks away and hundreds of miles
up a river that snaked through the war,

09:37.160 --> 09:38.703
like a main circuit cable

09:39.204 --> 09:40.997
plugged straight into Kurtz.

09:44.667 --> 09:47.253
It was no accident
that I got to be the caretaker

09:47.337 --> 09:49.380
of Colonel Walter E. Kurtz's memory...

09:49.964 --> 09:52.842
any more than being back
in Saigon was an accident.

09:55.011 --> 09:58.014
There is no way to tell his story
without telling my own,

09:59.307 --> 10:01.267
and if his story is really a confession...

10:01.392 --> 10:02.519
Capt. Willard reporting, sir.

10:02.602 --> 10:03.645
...then so is mine.

10:03.770 --> 10:06.064
Captain, good. Come on in.

10:06.189 --> 10:07.065
[Willard] Thank you, sir.

10:07.440 --> 10:08.316
Stand at ease.

10:08.942 --> 10:11.694
[piano music playing]

10:12.529 --> 10:13.404
Want a cigarette?

10:15.198 --> 10:16.157
No, thank you, sir.

10:18.326 --> 10:20.411
Captain, have you ever seen this gentleman
before?

10:21.204 --> 10:22.080
No, sir.

10:22.455 --> 10:23.998
Met the general or myself?

10:24.666 --> 10:25.875
No, sir, not personally.

10:27.877 --> 10:30.255
[Lucas] You've worked a lot on your own,
haven't you, Captain?

10:30.338 --> 10:31.256
Yes, sir, I have.

10:31.422 --> 10:32.841
[Lucas]
Your report specifies intelligence,

10:32.924 --> 10:34.926
counter-intelligence with COMSEC I Corps.

10:35.552 --> 10:38.138
I'm not presently disposed to discuss
those operations, sir.

10:47.480 --> 10:49.899
Did you not work for the CIA and I Corps?

10:52.068 --> 10:52.944
No, sir.

10:53.236 --> 10:55.613
Did you not assassinate
a government tax collector,

10:56.030 --> 10:58.408
Quang Tri province, June 18, 1968?

11:01.661 --> 11:02.579
Captain?

11:04.372 --> 11:08.877
Sir, I am unaware of
any such activity or operation...

11:09.752 --> 11:10.670
[clears throat]

11:10.837 --> 11:11.921
...nor would I...

11:13.256 --> 11:17.844
be disposed to discuss such an operation,
if it did in fact exist, sir.

11:29.731 --> 11:31.983
I thought we'd have a bite
of lunch while we talk.

11:32.108 --> 11:34.319
I hope you brought a good appetite,
Captain.

11:35.820 --> 11:37.405
I noticed that you have a...

11:39.657 --> 11:41.326
A bad hand there, are you wounded?

11:41.576 --> 11:43.828
[Willard] I had a little fishing accident
on R and R, sir.

11:43.995 --> 11:45.622
[Corman] Fishing on R and R?

11:45.788 --> 11:46.664
Yes, sir.

11:47.081 --> 11:49.083
But you're feeling fit,
you're ready for duty?

11:49.584 --> 11:51.002
Yes, General, very much so, sir.

11:52.212 --> 11:57.175
Well, let's see what we have here.
Roast beef, and usually it's not bad.

11:59.219 --> 12:01.387
Try some, Jerry, and pass it around.

12:02.430 --> 12:05.225
[Corman] To save a little time,
we might pass both ways.

12:06.684 --> 12:07.560
Uh...

12:08.895 --> 12:12.357
Captain, I don't know how you feel
about this shrimp, but...

12:13.650 --> 12:16.778
if you'll eat it, you'll never have to
prove your courage in any other way.

12:18.696 --> 12:21.407
Ah, well, why don't I just take
a piece here?

12:22.575 --> 12:25.703
[Lucas] Captain, you've heard of
Colonel Walter E. Kurtz?

12:27.705 --> 12:30.124
Um...Yes, sir, I've heard the name.

12:30.500 --> 12:32.210
Oh, Jesus.

12:32.460 --> 12:34.963
Operations officer, 5th Special Forces.

12:35.380 --> 12:37.131
Luke, would you play that tape

12:37.257 --> 12:39.259
-for the captain, please?
-[Lucas] Yes, sir. Sorry, sir.

12:39.342 --> 12:40.969
[Corman]
Listen to this carefully, carefully.

12:44.138 --> 12:47.058
[Kurtz] Central to 9, 04:30 hours.
Sector Peter Victor King.

12:47.141 --> 12:48.559
This was monitored out of Cambodia.

12:50.770 --> 12:53.064
This has been verified
as Colonel Kurtz's voice.

12:53.147 --> 12:55.984
[Kurtz] I watched a snail...

12:57.402 --> 12:58.820
crawl along the edge...

13:00.405 --> 13:01.531
of a straight razor.

13:03.783 --> 13:04.826
That's my dream.

13:07.412 --> 13:08.663
That's my nightmare...

13:11.833 --> 13:13.501
crawling, slithering...

13:14.919 --> 13:15.837
along the edge...

13:18.172 --> 13:21.426
of a straight razor...

13:23.761 --> 13:25.013
and surviving.

13:28.141 --> 13:32.353
[soldier] Transmission 11, received 68,
December 30, 05:00 hours,

13:32.729 --> 13:33.980
Sector King Zulu King.

13:36.399 --> 13:37.567
[Kurtz] But we must kill them.

13:38.651 --> 13:40.194
We must incinerate them...

13:41.154 --> 13:42.572
pig after pig...

13:43.990 --> 13:45.491
cow after cow...

13:47.744 --> 13:49.203
village after village...

13:49.829 --> 13:51.080
army after army.

13:52.540 --> 13:54.667
And they call me an assassin.

13:55.043 --> 13:56.127
What do you call it

13:57.045 --> 13:59.297
when the assassins accuse the assassin?

14:00.631 --> 14:01.549
They lie.

14:02.550 --> 14:04.635
They lie, and we have to be merciful.

14:05.428 --> 14:06.429
For those who lie,

14:08.014 --> 14:10.892
those Nabobs...

14:12.977 --> 14:13.853
I hate them.

14:15.938 --> 14:17.106
I do hate them.

14:23.196 --> 14:26.032
Walt Kurtz was one of the most
outstanding officers

14:26.282 --> 14:27.367
this country's ever produced.

14:28.743 --> 14:30.745
He was brilliant.
He was outstanding in every way.

14:32.747 --> 14:34.874
And he was a good man, too,

14:35.875 --> 14:36.793
a humanitarian man,

14:38.836 --> 14:40.254
a man of wit and humor.

14:41.756 --> 14:43.299
He joined the special forces,

14:45.927 --> 14:47.470
and after that, his...

14:49.889 --> 14:50.807
ideas...

14:51.933 --> 14:52.809
methods...

14:55.061 --> 14:55.937
became...

14:58.981 --> 14:59.857
unsound.

15:05.655 --> 15:06.531
Unsound.

15:12.787 --> 15:14.747
[Lucas] Now he's crossed into Cambodia
with this...

15:15.748 --> 15:18.042
Montagnard army of his that worship...

15:18.751 --> 15:20.503
the man like a god

15:21.587 --> 15:24.590
and follow every order,
however ridiculous.

15:26.801 --> 15:28.052
[Corman] Well, I have some other...

15:29.470 --> 15:30.596
shocking news to tell you.

15:31.431 --> 15:33.266
Colonel Kurtz was about to be...

15:34.559 --> 15:35.643
arrested for murder.

15:37.311 --> 15:38.479
I don't follow, sir.

15:39.480 --> 15:40.356
Murdered who?

15:40.481 --> 15:44.318
Kurtz had ordered the execution
of some Vietnamese intelligence agents,

15:44.819 --> 15:46.988
men he believed were double agents.

15:48.865 --> 15:50.741
So he took matters into his own hands.

15:53.453 --> 15:54.954
Well, you see, Willard,

15:56.706 --> 15:58.124
in this war, things get...

15:59.959 --> 16:01.169
confused out there.

16:02.962 --> 16:08.092
Power, ideals, the old morality,
and practical military necessity.

16:11.345 --> 16:13.097
But out there with these natives,

16:14.974 --> 16:18.186
it must be a temptation to...

16:19.687 --> 16:20.563
be God.

16:24.609 --> 16:27.195
Because there's a conflict
in every human heart,

16:28.863 --> 16:30.573
between the rational and irrational,

16:32.533 --> 16:33.618
between good and evil,

16:35.995 --> 16:37.788
and good does not always triumph.

16:41.000 --> 16:42.084
Sometimes...

16:44.045 --> 16:45.046
the dark side

16:46.339 --> 16:49.800
overcomes what Lincoln called
"the better angels of our nature."

16:52.553 --> 16:54.472
Every man has got a breaking point.

16:55.890 --> 16:57.058
You and I have them.

16:59.435 --> 17:01.020
Walt Kurtz has reached his...

17:03.439 --> 17:05.900
and, very obviously, he has gone insane.

17:09.987 --> 17:13.407
[helicopter whirs]

17:19.497 --> 17:20.373
Yes, sir.

17:20.540 --> 17:23.000
[clears throats] Very much so, sir.
Obviously insane.

17:27.922 --> 17:31.676
Your mission is to proceed
up the Nung River, in a Navy patrol boat.

17:31.759 --> 17:32.635
[clears throat]

17:33.427 --> 17:35.972
Pick up Colonel Kurtz's path
at Nu Mung Ba,

17:36.806 --> 17:38.724
follow it, learn what you can
along the way.

17:39.850 --> 17:42.311
When you find the colonel,
infiltrate his team

17:42.436 --> 17:45.022
by... [clears throat]
...whatever means available

17:46.023 --> 17:47.775
and terminate the colonel's command.

17:54.448 --> 17:56.909
Terminate... the colonel?

17:58.035 --> 18:01.872
He's out there
operating without any decent restraint,

18:02.456 --> 18:07.295
totally beyond the pale of
any acceptable human conduct

18:08.671 --> 18:10.881
and he's still in the field,
commanding troops.

18:12.883 --> 18:13.843
Terminate...

18:14.802 --> 18:16.095
with extreme prejudice.

18:18.014 --> 18:21.601
[Lucas] You understand, Captain,
that this mission does not exist...

18:23.352 --> 18:24.812
nor will it ever exist.

19:20.409 --> 19:22.286
[Willard] How many people
had I already killed?

19:24.246 --> 19:26.415
There were those six
that I knew about for sure...

19:28.209 --> 19:30.795
close enough to blow their last breath
in my face.

19:33.589 --> 19:36.050
But this time, it was an American

19:37.385 --> 19:38.427
and an officer.

19:50.147 --> 19:52.233
That wasn't supposed to make
any difference to me,

19:53.192 --> 19:54.193
but it did.

19:57.029 --> 19:57.905
Shit...

19:58.739 --> 20:00.574
charging a man with murder in this place

20:00.658 --> 20:03.494
was like handing out speeding tickets
at the Indy 500.

20:06.330 --> 20:07.373
I took the mission.

20:08.165 --> 20:09.875
What the hell else was I going to do?

20:12.336 --> 20:14.797
But I really didn't know
what I'd do when I found him.

20:28.811 --> 20:31.939
I was being ferried down the coast
in a Navy PBR,

20:32.398 --> 20:34.108
a type of plastic patrol boat,

20:34.358 --> 20:35.818
pretty common sight on the rivers.

20:37.111 --> 20:39.155
They said it was a good way
to pick up information

20:39.238 --> 20:41.031
and move without drawing
a lot of attention.

20:42.116 --> 20:43.117
That was okay.

20:43.951 --> 20:45.494
I needed the air and the time.

20:47.496 --> 20:49.415
Only problem was, I wouldn't be alone.

20:49.582 --> 20:50.499
Morning, Captain.

20:53.836 --> 20:55.796
The crew were mostly just kids,

20:57.047 --> 20:59.467
rock 'n' rollers with one foot
in their graves.

21:01.218 --> 21:02.261
How old are you?

21:02.803 --> 21:03.721
Seventeen.

21:05.097 --> 21:07.808
[Willard] The machinist, the one they
called "Chef", was from New Orleans.

21:08.434 --> 21:10.311
He was wrapped too tight for Vietnam...

21:11.395 --> 21:13.272
probably wrapped too tight
for New Orleans.

21:14.273 --> 21:16.525
Lance, on the forward 50s,
was a famous surfer

21:16.609 --> 21:18.194
from the beaches south of L.A.

21:19.111 --> 21:21.947
To look at him, you wouldn't believe
he'd ever fired a weapon in his life.

21:24.950 --> 21:29.205
"Clean", Mr. Clean, was from
some South Bronx shit-hole

21:29.288 --> 21:31.415
and I think the light and space of Vietnam

21:31.499 --> 21:32.917
really put the zap on his head.

21:36.629 --> 21:38.255
Then there was Phillips, the chief.

21:39.131 --> 21:40.466
It might have been my mission...

21:40.883 --> 21:42.635
but it sure as shit was the chief's boat.

21:43.010 --> 21:44.136
There's about two points

21:44.220 --> 21:46.597
where we can draw enough water
to get into the Nung River.

21:47.723 --> 21:48.641
They're both hot.

21:48.933 --> 21:49.850
Belong to Charlie.

21:51.977 --> 21:52.978
Don't worry about it.

21:54.396 --> 21:55.356
I don't smoke.

21:57.650 --> 21:59.735
You know,
I pulled a few special ops in here.

22:01.070 --> 22:02.321
About six months ago,

22:03.656 --> 22:06.450
I took a man who was going up
past the bridge at Do Lung.

22:08.118 --> 22:09.411
He was regular army, too.

22:12.748 --> 22:14.250
I heard he shot himself in the head.

22:17.545 --> 22:20.381
[radio plays]

22:24.093 --> 22:26.428
♪ It's the central highlands AFVN ♪

22:26.512 --> 22:28.013
♪ Man, it's really hot ♪

22:30.224 --> 22:31.225
[Johnson] Good morning, Vietnam.

22:31.392 --> 22:33.894
I'm Army Specialist Zack Johnson on AFVN.

22:33.978 --> 22:36.480
It's about 82 degrees in downtown Saigon
right now,

22:36.564 --> 22:37.648
also very humid.

22:37.857 --> 22:41.068
And we have an important message
for all GIs who are living off base,

22:41.151 --> 22:43.028
-from the mayor of Saigon
-Yeah!

22:43.195 --> 22:46.282
He'd like you to hang your laundry up
indoors, instead of on the window sills.

22:46.365 --> 22:48.659
The mayor wants you to keep
Saigon beautiful.

22:49.952 --> 22:52.454
And now, here's another blast
from the past, going out to big Sam,

22:52.538 --> 22:54.206
who's all alone in the mantle room
out there

22:54.331 --> 22:56.083
with the 1st Battalion, 35th Infantry,

22:56.375 --> 22:58.377
and dedicated by the fire team
at An Khage,

22:58.460 --> 23:00.629
to their groovy CO, Brent, "the hip."

23:00.754 --> 23:03.674
-The Rolling Stones, "Satisfaction".
-Ooh. All right!

23:03.841 --> 23:05.342
["Satisfaction"
by The Rolling Stones plays]

23:05.467 --> 23:06.802
Watch out, Clean!

23:08.137 --> 23:09.513
Get down, Bubba!

23:12.600 --> 23:15.603
♪ I can't get no ♪

23:16.061 --> 23:18.689
♪ Satisfaction ♪

23:19.231 --> 23:20.149
Hang on, Lance!

23:20.357 --> 23:22.234
♪ I can't get no ♪

23:22.359 --> 23:23.360
[villagers shout]

23:23.485 --> 23:25.321
♪ Satisfaction ♪

23:25.404 --> 23:26.530
♪ 'Cause I try ♪

23:26.614 --> 23:27.489
Oh! Oh! Oh!

23:27.615 --> 23:29.408
[Chief] Pipe down, Bubba!

23:30.743 --> 23:32.161
♪ And I try ♪

23:32.244 --> 23:34.872
♪ I can't get no ♪

23:36.206 --> 23:37.917
♪ I can't get no ♪

23:39.793 --> 23:42.546
♪ When I'm driving in my car ♪

23:42.880 --> 23:46.550
♪ And a man comes on the radio ♪

23:47.134 --> 23:49.511
♪ He's tellin' me more and more ♪

23:50.095 --> 23:53.223
♪ About some useless information ♪

23:53.307 --> 23:56.977
-♪ Supposed to drive my imagination... ♪
-Workout! Yeah! Yeah! Yeah!

23:57.311 --> 23:58.187
[Chief] All right!

23:59.647 --> 24:00.898
[Clean] Look out, Lance!

24:02.858 --> 24:04.276
[Lance] Sayonara!

24:17.498 --> 24:20.459
[Willard] At first, I thought
they handed me the wrong dossier.

24:21.377 --> 24:23.629
I couldn't believe
they wanted this man dead.

24:25.756 --> 24:27.424
Third generation West Point,

24:27.549 --> 24:30.511
top of his class, Korea, Airborne,

24:31.011 --> 24:32.513
about a thousand decorations,

24:33.097 --> 24:34.682
et cetera, et cetera.

24:37.685 --> 24:41.188
I'd heard his voice on the tape,
and it really put the hook in me,

24:42.690 --> 24:46.402
but I couldn't connect up that voice
with this man.

24:53.492 --> 24:55.911
Like they said,
he had an impressive career,

24:57.329 --> 24:58.580
maybe too impressive,

25:00.207 --> 25:01.333
I mean perfect.

25:02.793 --> 25:06.046
He was being groomed for one
of the top slots in the corporation,

25:06.630 --> 25:09.591
General, Chief of Staff, anything.

25:11.802 --> 25:15.848
In 1964, he returned from a tour
with Advisory Command in Vietnam,

25:15.973 --> 25:17.057
and things started to slip.

25:18.392 --> 25:22.438
His report to the joint Chiefs of Staff
and Lyndon Johnson was restricted.

25:24.982 --> 25:26.817
Seems they didn't dig
what he had to tell 'em.

25:28.652 --> 25:31.488
During the next few months,
he made three requests for transfer

25:31.572 --> 25:33.907
to Airborne training, Fort Benning,
Georgia,

25:34.867 --> 25:36.285
and was finally accepted.

25:39.538 --> 25:40.706
Airborne.

25:43.709 --> 25:45.377
He was 38 years old.

25:47.504 --> 25:49.048
Why the fuck would he do that?

25:52.051 --> 25:55.345
"1966, joins Special Forces,

25:56.388 --> 25:57.765
returns, Vietnam."

25:58.474 --> 25:59.516
[distant explosion]

25:59.641 --> 26:00.684
Hey, what's that?

26:00.768 --> 26:01.685
[Willard] Arc light.

26:01.769 --> 26:02.644
What's up?

26:03.312 --> 26:04.480
[Willard] B-52 strike.

26:06.273 --> 26:07.232
[Chef] What's that?

26:07.316 --> 26:08.192
Arc light.

26:08.275 --> 26:11.153
[Chef] I hate that. Every time
I hear that, something terrible happens.

26:11.236 --> 26:13.280
[Clean] Charlie don't ever see 'em
or hear 'em, man.

26:13.363 --> 26:14.281
[Lance] There they are!

26:14.364 --> 26:16.658
[Clean] Concussion'll suck the air
out of your damn lungs.

26:17.367 --> 26:19.078
[Chef] Something terrible's gonna happen.

26:19.161 --> 26:20.037
Smoke!

26:20.537 --> 26:22.039
Secondary burn.

26:22.748 --> 26:24.666
[Chief] Hueys over there,
lots of Hueys.

26:24.750 --> 26:26.126
[Willard] Let's have a look, Chief.

26:29.296 --> 26:31.882
It was the Air Cav, 1st of the 9th.

26:32.049 --> 26:33.383
That's them.

26:33.467 --> 26:35.594
Our escorts to the mouth
of the Nung River.

26:36.053 --> 26:39.348
But they were supposed to be waiting
for us another 30 kilometers ahead.

26:39.973 --> 26:44.144
Well, Air Mobile,
those boys just couldn't stay put.

26:45.187 --> 26:46.647
[child crying]

26:48.565 --> 26:50.692
[helicopters whirring]

26:57.950 --> 26:59.701
[soldier] Come on, get down. Come on.

27:06.583 --> 27:07.459
[splash]

27:11.588 --> 27:13.924
1st of the 9th was
an old cavalry division.

27:14.007 --> 27:15.843
Then it cashed in its horses for choppers

27:15.926 --> 27:18.637
and going tear-assing round 'Nam
looking for the shit.

27:19.972 --> 27:22.850
They'd given Charlie a few surprises
in their time here.

27:24.685 --> 27:27.938
What they were mopping up now
hadn't even happened yet an hour ago.

27:28.021 --> 27:29.606
[explosion]

27:29.857 --> 27:31.942
[director] Just keep running by.
We're for television,

27:32.025 --> 27:34.278
we're all getting back. Just keep going.
Go on, keep going.

27:34.361 --> 27:36.113
It's for television.
Don't look at the camera.

27:36.238 --> 27:38.574
Don't look at the camera,
just go by like you're fighting.

27:38.657 --> 27:40.576
Like you're fighting,
don't look at the camera.

27:40.742 --> 27:43.120
-It's for television, just go through.
-[helicopters whirring]

27:43.287 --> 27:45.247
Just go by, keep on going.
Don't look toward it.

27:45.372 --> 27:47.749
Keep going, don't look at the camera.
Go on, keep going.

28:11.815 --> 28:13.233
Where can I find the CO?

28:13.358 --> 28:15.068
You can't miss him, sir, he's over there.

28:17.863 --> 28:20.073
We're all right for the tanks.
It's all right, Captain.

28:21.366 --> 28:26.079
Captain Willard. I carry priority papers
from COMSEC Intelligence II Corps.

28:26.496 --> 28:29.917
I understand that Trang has briefed you
on the requirements of my mission.

28:30.167 --> 28:32.211
What mission?
I haven't heard from Nah Trang.

28:32.920 --> 28:35.422
Sir, your unit is supposed to escort us
into the Nung.

28:35.839 --> 28:37.174
Well, we'll see what we can do,

28:37.299 --> 28:39.509
but just stay out of my way
'til this is done, Captain.

28:40.135 --> 28:41.887
[explosion]

28:45.390 --> 28:48.018
All right. Let's see what we have,
let's see what we have.

28:48.477 --> 28:49.478
Two of spades.

28:49.978 --> 28:51.104
Three of spades.

28:51.355 --> 28:52.231
Four of diamonds.

28:53.565 --> 28:54.566
Six of clubs.

28:55.359 --> 28:56.443
Eight of spades.

28:57.194 --> 28:59.363
There isn't one worth a Jack
in the whole bunch.

29:02.658 --> 29:04.576
[Chef] Hey, Captain, what's that?

29:04.910 --> 29:05.869
[Willard] Death cards.

29:06.453 --> 29:07.329
[Chef] What?

29:08.205 --> 29:09.331
Death cards.

29:09.581 --> 29:11.375
Let’s Charlie know who did this.

29:16.004 --> 29:16.880
Cheer up, son.

29:16.964 --> 29:18.966
[man over speakerphone]
We will not hurt you or harm you.

29:19.049 --> 29:20.592
[soldier] Fire in the hole!

29:21.176 --> 29:22.344
[explosion]

29:22.511 --> 29:24.221
[man over speakerphone]
We are here to help you.

29:24.388 --> 29:27.432
[speaking Vietnamese over speakerphone]

29:27.724 --> 29:30.519
We are here to extend a welcome hand...

29:30.602 --> 29:31.520
[Kilgore] Come on.

29:31.603 --> 29:32.938
...to those of you who would like...

29:33.021 --> 29:33.897
[Kilgore] Everybody in?

29:33.981 --> 29:36.650
...to return to the heart
of the South Vietnamese government.

29:37.985 --> 29:39.194
[Kilgore] Get in. Hurry up.

29:40.821 --> 29:41.738
[Kilgore whistles]

29:42.489 --> 29:43.615
Move it out.

29:48.328 --> 29:51.081
Hey! [whistles]
Hey, what's this?

29:52.958 --> 29:53.875
What is this?

29:54.418 --> 29:56.962
[soldier] This man's hurt pretty bad, sir.

29:57.254 --> 30:00.674
About the only thing that's holding
his guts in is that pot lid.

30:01.008 --> 30:02.384
What do you have to say?

30:03.260 --> 30:05.053
This one here is dirty VC.

30:05.846 --> 30:06.722
He wants water.

30:07.055 --> 30:08.932
He can drink paddy water.

30:10.267 --> 30:11.268
Get out of here!

30:11.560 --> 30:12.894
Give me that, give me that canteen!

30:12.978 --> 30:14.688
[Vietnamese Soldier]
VC, he's a VC, you know!

30:14.771 --> 30:18.567
Any man brave enough to-- Get out of here!
Before I kick your fucking ass!

30:18.650 --> 30:20.610
[Vietnamese soldier]
He killing a lot of our people!

30:20.694 --> 30:23.363
Any man brave enough to fight
with his guts strapped up

30:23.447 --> 30:24.948
can drink from my canteen any day.

30:25.073 --> 30:28.452
Hey, Colonel, I think one of those sailors
is Lance Johnson, the surfer.

30:28.702 --> 30:30.162
Where, here in Chua?

30:30.537 --> 30:31.538
Down there.

30:32.831 --> 30:33.832
Straight ahead?

30:35.375 --> 30:37.127
[soldier] Repeat. We have a body count...

30:41.256 --> 30:42.424
What's your name, sailor?

30:43.175 --> 30:45.177
Gunner's Mate, third class,
L. Johnson, sir.

30:45.260 --> 30:46.136
Gunner's Mate, third--

30:46.219 --> 30:47.804
All right! Lance Johnson, the surfer?

30:48.680 --> 30:49.556
Yes, sir.

30:50.390 --> 30:54.019
Well, it's an honor to meet you, Lance.
I've admired your nose-riding for years.

30:54.519 --> 30:57.314
I like your cutback, too.
I think you're the best cutback there is.

30:57.522 --> 30:58.482
Hey, thank you, sir.

30:58.732 --> 31:02.194
Well, you cut the "sir" crap, Lance.
I'm Bill Kilgore, I'm a goofy foot.

31:02.402 --> 31:03.779
-This guy with you?
-Yeah.

31:06.365 --> 31:08.158
-This is Mike from San Diego,
-Far out.

31:08.408 --> 31:09.409
Johnny from Malibu.

31:09.659 --> 31:11.536
-John, hi. Far out.
-We're pretty solid surfers.

31:11.620 --> 31:13.705
None of us are
anywhere near your class, though.

31:13.789 --> 31:14.664
No way!

31:15.207 --> 31:18.752
We do a lot of surfing around here, Lance,
I like to finish operations early,

31:18.960 --> 31:21.338
fly down to Yung Tau
for the evening glass.

31:31.181 --> 31:33.809
[priest] Through him in the unity
of the holy spirit.

31:34.017 --> 31:37.813
All glory and honor is yours,
almighty Father. Amen.

31:37.938 --> 31:40.148
-[explosion]
-Let us pray with confidence in the father

31:40.232 --> 31:42.025
and the words our savior gave us.

31:42.317 --> 31:44.694
-[helicopters whirring]
-[all] Our father who art in heaven,

31:44.820 --> 31:46.196
hallowed be thy name.

31:46.530 --> 31:50.909
Thy kingdom come, thy will be done
on earth as it is in heaven.

31:53.412 --> 31:55.163
[cow moos]

32:11.972 --> 32:14.349
[Willard] Kilgore'd had a pretty good day
for himself.

32:15.183 --> 32:17.436
They choppered in the T-bones and the beer

32:17.519 --> 32:19.396
and turned the L.Z. Into a beach party.

32:21.064 --> 32:23.400
The more they tried to make it
just like home,

32:23.900 --> 32:25.694
the more they made everybody miss it.

32:26.319 --> 32:29.281
[Kilgore] Make my meat rare.
Rare, but not cold!

32:29.781 --> 32:32.284
[singing and playing guitar]

32:35.829 --> 32:38.290
Well, he wasn't a bad officer, I guess.

32:38.582 --> 32:39.499
[clapping]

32:39.583 --> 32:42.502
He loved his boys
and you felt safe with him.

32:43.253 --> 32:46.131
He was one of those guys that had
that weird light around him.

32:46.756 --> 32:49.718
You just knew he wasn't going to get
so much as a scratch here.

32:50.010 --> 32:51.511
What happened to your mission, Captain?

32:51.887 --> 32:54.514
-Nha Trang forget all about you?
-[laughing]

33:02.397 --> 33:03.982
-[Kilgore] Here, boy.
-[laughs]

33:05.275 --> 33:06.193
Sir?

33:06.902 --> 33:09.404
-Two places we can get into the river.
-Yep.

33:09.696 --> 33:11.698
-Here and here.
-[Kilgore] Mm-hmm.

33:11.781 --> 33:14.743
It's a pretty wide delta, but these are
the only two spots I'm really sure of.

33:16.828 --> 33:19.206
Well, that village you're pointing at
is kinda hairy, Willard.

33:20.081 --> 33:21.208
What do you mean hairy, sir?

33:21.333 --> 33:23.627
It's hairy,
got some pretty heavy ordnance.

33:24.252 --> 33:26.588
I lost a few recon ships in there,
now and again.

33:27.297 --> 33:29.633
What's the name of that God damn village?
Vinh Drin...

33:30.258 --> 33:31.468
-[soldier] Drap?
-Dop or Lop

33:32.677 --> 33:34.596
Damn Gook names all sound the same.

33:36.723 --> 33:38.975
Mike, you know anything about
this point at Vinh Drin Dop?

33:40.143 --> 33:41.686
That's a fantastic peak.

33:42.270 --> 33:43.146
Peak?

33:43.230 --> 33:45.732
About 6 foot.
Yeah, it's an outstanding peak.

33:45.857 --> 33:49.194
It's got both a long right and left
slide, with a bowl section.

33:49.277 --> 33:50.946
It's unbelievable. It's just tube city.

33:53.114 --> 33:55.033
[distant explosions]

33:55.784 --> 33:57.869
Well, why didn't you tell me that before?
A good peak.

33:57.953 --> 34:00.121
There aren't any good peaks
in this whole shitty country.

34:00.539 --> 34:02.457
It's all God damn beach break.

34:02.541 --> 34:04.918
It's really hairy in there, sir.
That's where we lost McDonald.

34:05.001 --> 34:08.129
They shot the hell out of us there.
That's Charlie's point.

34:08.296 --> 34:09.798
[distant explosions]

34:09.923 --> 34:11.883
Sir, we can go in there tomorrow at dawn.

34:12.759 --> 34:14.761
There's always a good offshore breeze
in the morning.

34:15.136 --> 34:17.180
It'd mean I'd be able
to get the boat in,

34:17.264 --> 34:19.558
the draft at the mouth of that river
may be too shallow.

34:20.559 --> 34:22.978
Hell, we'll pick your boat up
and put it down like a baby

34:23.061 --> 34:26.273
right where you want it.
This is the 1st of the 9th. Air Cav, son.

34:26.398 --> 34:27.274
Air Mobile.

34:28.275 --> 34:30.860
I can take that point and hold it
just as long as I like

34:30.944 --> 34:33.572
and you can get anyplace up that river
that suits you, young Captain.

34:34.239 --> 34:36.449
Hell, a 6-foot peak.
[laughs]

34:36.533 --> 34:37.784
[soldier laughs]

34:38.034 --> 34:39.995
I'd like to take a gunship
back to the division.

34:40.078 --> 34:40.954
Lance, go with Mike.

34:41.037 --> 34:44.124
Let him pick out a board for you
and bring me my Yater Spoon, the 8'6".

34:44.207 --> 34:46.209
-[soldier] I don't know, sir, it's--
-What is it, soldier?

34:46.793 --> 34:49.337
Well, I mean, it's pretty hairy in there.
That's Charlie's point.

34:49.546 --> 34:50.880
Charlie don't surf!

34:51.673 --> 34:55.010
[helicopters whirring]

35:15.572 --> 35:18.033
Hey, Jesus, Clean,
you ain't going to believe this. Look.

35:19.909 --> 35:22.495
[Clean] Hey, man,
they're picking up the boat!

35:25.874 --> 35:27.292
[Kilgore] How're you feeling, Jimmy?

35:27.459 --> 35:29.294
Like a mean motherfucker, sir!

35:31.838 --> 35:33.673
All right, son, let her rip.

35:34.549 --> 35:36.217
-[bugle sounds charge]
-[Kilgore] Let's go!

36:58.800 --> 37:00.885
[Kilgore]
I never have got used to a light board.

37:01.261 --> 37:03.471
I can't get used to 'em,
I'm used to a heavy board.

37:03.596 --> 37:04.723
I know, it's a real drag.

37:05.557 --> 37:07.934
Do you use--
Do you prefer a heavy or a light board?

37:08.017 --> 37:08.893
Heavier.

37:08.977 --> 37:10.228
-Really?
-Yeah.

37:10.311 --> 37:12.564
I thought
the young guys liked lighter boards?

37:12.689 --> 37:16.025
-You can't ride the nose on those things--
-[man over radio] Big duke 6, this is

37:16.151 --> 37:17.944
Eagle Thrust 7. We've got it spotted.

37:18.027 --> 37:21.281
Big Duke 6 to Eagle Thrust.
Put on heading 2-7-0.

37:21.364 --> 37:22.782
Assume attack formation.

37:23.074 --> 37:24.701
[man over radio]
That's a roger, Big Duke.

37:24.826 --> 37:26.494
-Okay, we're going in.
-Hey, Lance.

37:27.287 --> 37:29.497
We'll come in low out of the rising sun

37:29.914 --> 37:32.167
and about a mile out,
we'll put on the music.

37:32.375 --> 37:33.251
Music?

37:33.418 --> 37:36.713
Yeah, I use Wagner.
It scares the hell out of the slopes.

37:37.005 --> 37:38.339
My boys love it.

37:38.923 --> 37:40.884
[Lance] Hey! They're going to play music!

37:47.974 --> 37:50.310
How come all you guys sit on your helmet?

37:51.561 --> 37:54.022
So we don't get our balls blown off.

37:55.857 --> 37:57.776
[Chef laughs]

38:05.617 --> 38:07.368
Big Duke 6 to Eagle Thrust.

38:08.119 --> 38:10.455
Put on psy-war-op. Make it loud.

38:10.955 --> 38:13.792
Bit of the Romeo Foxtrot, shall we dance?

38:14.125 --> 38:17.587
["Ride of the Valkyries" by Wagner plays]

38:19.631 --> 38:21.633
The surf!
[laughs]

38:37.732 --> 38:41.110
["Ride of the Valkyries" continues]

39:05.969 --> 39:08.179
[inaudible]

39:29.200 --> 39:30.451
[dog barking]

39:38.710 --> 39:41.713
[children singing in Vietnamese]

39:46.426 --> 39:49.178
[shouting in Vietnamese]

39:49.387 --> 39:51.347
["Ride of the Valkyries"
plays in the distance]

39:51.472 --> 39:54.934
[bell rings]

40:06.279 --> 40:09.240
["Ride of the Valkyries" continues]

40:31.304 --> 40:32.430
[explosion]

40:33.890 --> 40:36.559
[machine gun fire]

40:36.684 --> 40:39.187
[explosions]

40:45.610 --> 40:46.569
[explosion]

40:48.905 --> 40:50.365
[machine gun fire]

40:50.615 --> 40:52.158
[explosions]

40:58.539 --> 40:59.624
[gunshots]

40:59.832 --> 41:01.459
Run, Charlie!

41:04.587 --> 41:06.589
[pilot over radio]
There's something coming in...

41:08.299 --> 41:10.510
[machine gun fire]

41:11.344 --> 41:14.722
[explosions]

41:16.933 --> 41:17.809
[gunshots]

41:20.895 --> 41:23.064
[gunshots]

41:23.147 --> 41:24.607
[Kilgore] There, an automatic 50 cal!

41:24.732 --> 41:25.775
50 cal in the open!

41:26.359 --> 41:28.277
[pilot over headset]
Spotted a large weapon down below.

41:28.444 --> 41:30.405
We're gonna go down and check it out.

41:30.488 --> 41:34.409
[machine gun fire]

41:34.993 --> 41:36.285
[explosion]

41:36.411 --> 41:37.537
[gunshots]

41:41.499 --> 41:42.834
[explosion]

41:43.126 --> 41:44.210
Right! What a shot!

41:44.293 --> 41:46.462
[Kilgore] Outstanding,
red team, outstanding.

41:46.587 --> 41:48.339
Get you a case of beer for that one.

41:53.678 --> 41:55.888
[gunshots]

42:09.652 --> 42:11.988
[pilot] 6-4-1-0.
We're over the village right now

42:12.113 --> 42:14.157
and I think I see a vehicle
down in the courtyard.

42:14.240 --> 42:15.199
I'm gonna check it out.

42:15.283 --> 42:16.951
Well done, Hawks, well done.

42:17.493 --> 42:20.163
I want some 20-Mike-Mike-Vulcan,
right along those tree-lines.

42:20.621 --> 42:22.165
-[gunshots]
-Ripple the shit out of them.

42:22.874 --> 42:25.126
We've got a vehicle on the bridge,
50 caliber on board,

42:25.209 --> 42:26.919
he's moving across to resupply the weapon.

42:28.546 --> 42:29.672
[Kilgore] Big Duke 6.

42:29.797 --> 42:32.759
Clear the area. I'm coming down myself.
These people never give up.

42:33.718 --> 42:36.012
[explosion]

42:37.638 --> 42:38.723
[Lance] Nice shot, Bill!

42:39.432 --> 42:41.017
[bullets thudding]

42:41.184 --> 42:42.268
[Kilgore] Whoa, whoa, whoa!

42:43.811 --> 42:46.773
[soldiers shouting]

42:47.774 --> 42:51.069
Un-ass that shit. Get it out of here!
Get it out, get it out!

42:51.152 --> 42:53.404
It's just a flare.
It's all right. Just a flare.

42:53.946 --> 42:55.907
Everybody all right?
Lance, you all right?

42:56.032 --> 42:56.908
[Lance] I'm fine!

43:10.379 --> 43:11.422
[explosion]

43:11.547 --> 43:13.049
[soldiers] Get down!

43:18.513 --> 43:20.348
[explosions]

43:22.600 --> 43:24.143
[gunshots]

43:25.978 --> 43:28.648
[gunshots]

43:33.653 --> 43:34.946
I'm not going!

43:35.071 --> 43:36.239
I'm not going!

43:36.531 --> 43:37.698
I'm not going!

43:39.492 --> 43:41.035
[gunshots]

43:41.119 --> 43:42.078
[explosion]

43:47.083 --> 43:48.209
[gunshots]

43:51.045 --> 43:52.046
[machine gun fire]

43:52.713 --> 43:54.882
[soldier over radio] We just got
secondaries down there on the plaza.

43:54.966 --> 43:57.135
[soldier 2 over radio] Blue-Green, Blue-4,
hold onto your positions.

43:57.260 --> 44:00.471
[soldier over radio] Duke 6, Duke 6.
We've got wounded down there.

44:01.556 --> 44:03.057
[soldiers shouting]

44:04.725 --> 44:07.979
[screams]
Oh, my god!

44:09.147 --> 44:10.189
Please, stop!

44:10.523 --> 44:11.524
Get a stretcher over here!

44:12.900 --> 44:14.360
I can't stand it!

44:15.570 --> 44:16.988
[speaking Vietnamese]

44:17.864 --> 44:19.991
Please, God, help me!

44:20.575 --> 44:21.492
[screams]

44:21.576 --> 44:22.493
Give him some morphine.

44:23.411 --> 44:25.913
0-3-7-7-4-2--

44:26.038 --> 44:27.498
Where's that stretcher?

44:27.832 --> 44:30.668
I want my wounded out of there
and in the hospital in 15 minutes

44:30.751 --> 44:32.295
and I want my men out.

44:32.420 --> 44:34.380
[soldier over radio] Somebody stay in
there tight with Big Duke.

44:34.630 --> 44:36.257
[soldier 2 over radio] This is 10-2.
We're gonna be in,

44:36.340 --> 44:39.594
throw 'em in and then get out.
So, the square's our way out.

44:55.610 --> 44:56.986
[Vietnamese girl] Ma! Ma!

45:00.656 --> 45:02.700
She's got a grenade! She's got a grenade!

45:02.783 --> 45:05.286
[explosion]

45:05.411 --> 45:07.955
[pilot over radio] Oh, Jesus!
The whole God damn thing's gone up.

45:08.122 --> 45:09.540
-Blew the shit out of it.
-Fuckin' savages.

45:09.957 --> 45:11.542
[screaming]

45:11.792 --> 45:13.294
[pilot over radio]
Wait 'til we get a medevac.

45:13.711 --> 45:14.879
[co-pilot over radio] Holy Christ!
She's a sap.

45:14.962 --> 45:16.547
I'm going to get that dink bitch.

45:16.631 --> 45:19.926
Get over there, Johnny. I'm rolling up,
put the right skid right up her ass.

45:20.009 --> 45:21.594
-[machine gun fire]
-[screams]

45:22.178 --> 45:23.387
We gotta get some air in these trees.

45:23.471 --> 45:25.181
It's God damn eat-up
with the enemy down there.

45:25.348 --> 45:27.391
I'm taking fire.
I'm taking hits all over.

45:28.059 --> 45:30.937
Three o'clock. Three o'clock, my position.
Drawing fire, drawing heavy fire.

45:31.729 --> 45:34.398
Mayday! Mayday! I'm going in.
My tail rotor's out, I got no control.

45:35.149 --> 45:36.817
[explosions]

45:38.986 --> 45:40.863
[explosions]

45:43.908 --> 45:44.951
What do you think?

45:45.034 --> 45:46.494
It's really exciting, man.

45:46.577 --> 45:47.912
No, no! The waves!

45:48.246 --> 45:49.121
The waves!

45:49.205 --> 45:50.206
[Lance] Oh, right.

45:50.289 --> 45:51.791
Look at that, breaks both ways. Watch.

45:51.916 --> 45:53.417
Watch!
[imitates waves crashing]

45:54.043 --> 45:56.379
Look! Good 6-foot swells!

46:09.934 --> 46:11.894
Go, men, pump it!

46:12.144 --> 46:13.688
[explosion]

46:19.485 --> 46:20.361
[Kilgore whistles]

46:20.486 --> 46:21.362
Come here, Lance.

46:24.991 --> 46:26.200
Incoming!

46:26.409 --> 46:27.368
[explosion]

46:27.994 --> 46:29.036
[explosion]

46:30.788 --> 46:33.874
This L.Z.'s still pretty hot, sir.
Maybe you ought to surf somewhere else.

46:33.958 --> 46:37.378
What do you know about surfing, Major?
You're from God damn New Jersey.

46:39.588 --> 46:41.590
[Kilgore whistles] Come here. Come here!

46:44.802 --> 46:45.678
Change.

46:45.886 --> 46:47.221
You mean right now, sir?

46:47.346 --> 46:50.141
I want to see how rideable that stuff is.
Go change!

46:50.266 --> 46:52.018
It's still pretty hairy out there, sir.

46:52.101 --> 46:53.352
You want to surf, soldier?

46:53.477 --> 46:54.353
Yes, sir.

46:54.437 --> 46:56.897
That's good, son,
'cause you either surf or fight.

46:56.981 --> 46:58.899
Is that clear? Now, get going.

46:59.400 --> 47:01.944
I'll cover for 'em.
Let's bring a board for Lance.

47:02.528 --> 47:03.404
[Kilgore whistles]

47:03.571 --> 47:05.698
[Willard] We can't do shit
until the boat gets here!

47:06.115 --> 47:06.991
Lance.

47:07.992 --> 47:09.660
I'll bet you can't wait to get out there.

47:09.827 --> 47:11.579
-What?
-See how they break both ways?

47:11.829 --> 47:15.750
One guy can break right, one left,
simultaneously. What do you think of that?

47:15.875 --> 47:18.127
I think we ought to wait
for the tide to come up.

47:18.252 --> 47:19.754
Hey, hey, Lance, come here. Look! Look!

47:19.837 --> 47:20.838
[soldier] Incoming!

47:20.963 --> 47:22.089
[explosion]

47:23.758 --> 47:26.218
The tide doesn't come in for six hours.

47:28.429 --> 47:30.264
You want to wait here for six hours?

47:34.268 --> 47:36.228
Yo! Hey! Chief!

47:44.111 --> 47:49.116
Okay, fellas, quit hiding.
Come on. Let's go, dickheads, take off.

47:49.200 --> 47:52.620
God damn it! Don't you think
it's a little risky for R and R?

47:53.079 --> 47:57.625
If I say it's safe to surf this beach,
Captain, it's safe to surf this beach.

47:57.708 --> 47:59.502
I mean, I'm not afraid to surf this place.

47:59.585 --> 48:01.796
-[explosion]
-I'll stay and surf this fucking place.

48:03.339 --> 48:04.215
[gunshots]

48:04.590 --> 48:05.883
Give me that R.T. soldier.

48:07.259 --> 48:08.260
[gunshots]

48:08.344 --> 48:09.845
Dove-4. This is Big Duke 6.

48:10.513 --> 48:13.349
God damn it. I want that tree line bombed.

48:13.557 --> 48:16.102
[pilot] Big Duke 6, roger.
Dove 13, standby.

48:16.477 --> 48:18.187
[Kilgore] Bomb it into the stone age, son.

48:18.396 --> 48:20.064
[pilot 1] Hawk 12, Dove 13, roger.

48:20.147 --> 48:21.941
They need some napalm
down near the tree line.

48:22.024 --> 48:23.901
Can you guys twist around
and put it down there?

48:23.984 --> 48:26.487
[pilot 2] Right, 1-3. We're fixed
to fuck with them, what's the target?

48:26.904 --> 48:29.865
[pilot 1] Trying to suppress some mortar
fire off the tree line down there.

48:30.157 --> 48:31.325
[pilot 2] Roger, here we come.

48:31.492 --> 48:35.079
[pilot 1] Good. Give it all you got.
Bring in all your ships, wing abreast.

48:37.373 --> 48:39.083
Don't worry.
We'll have this place cleaned up

48:39.166 --> 48:41.377
and ready for us in a jiffy, son,
don't you worry.

48:42.670 --> 48:45.089
[pilot] Big Duke 6, this is Dove 13.
The jets are inbound now.

48:45.172 --> 48:47.091
They got about 30 seconds to bomb station.

48:47.174 --> 48:48.634
Get your people back and heads down.

48:48.717 --> 48:49.844
This is gonna be a big one.

48:51.554 --> 48:55.099
[jet engines roaring]

48:57.768 --> 49:00.354
[Kilgore] Do you see that? Look.

49:00.479 --> 49:02.940
[explosions]

49:12.950 --> 49:13.868
Do you smell that?

49:15.035 --> 49:16.245
Do you smell that?

49:16.328 --> 49:17.204
What?

49:17.913 --> 49:18.998
Napalm, son.

49:20.082 --> 49:22.001
Nothing else
in the world smells like that.

49:22.960 --> 49:25.045
[soldier] Come on.
Move it! Move it! Move it! Move it!

49:25.379 --> 49:26.464
[helicopters whirring]

49:27.089 --> 49:28.966
I love the smell of napalm in the morning.

49:30.009 --> 49:32.636
You know, one time,
we had a hill bombed for 12 hours.

49:32.761 --> 49:34.305
When it was all over, I walked up.

49:35.347 --> 49:36.223
[distant explosion]

49:36.307 --> 49:38.934
We didn't find one of them,
not one stinking dink body.

49:41.479 --> 49:44.023
But the smell,
you know, that gasoline smell.

49:44.648 --> 49:45.608
The whole hill...

49:47.568 --> 49:48.444
it smelled like...

49:51.822 --> 49:52.740
victory.

49:55.826 --> 49:57.077
[explosion]

49:58.412 --> 49:59.872
Someday this war's going to end.

50:22.645 --> 50:23.521
Lance.

50:24.021 --> 50:26.690
[Clean] Chef, light up, man.
Come on, come on. Let's get high.

50:26.774 --> 50:28.692
-Wanna Smoke?
-[Clean] What you doing man, light up.

50:28.817 --> 50:30.444
[Willard] Someday this war's going to end.

50:32.238 --> 50:34.240
That'd be just fine
with the boys on the boat.

50:35.241 --> 50:37.326
They weren't looking for anything more
than a way home.

50:37.451 --> 50:38.410
[Chef] Captain?

50:39.203 --> 50:41.622
[Willard]
Trouble is, I've been back there,

50:42.706 --> 50:44.750
and I knew
that it just didn't exist anymore.

50:49.255 --> 50:50.214
[Lance] Buddha time.

50:51.840 --> 50:54.510
[Clean] All right. That's grass.
That's shit.

50:54.677 --> 50:55.553
Yeah.

51:00.391 --> 51:02.351
[Willard]
If that's how Kilgore fought the war,

51:03.018 --> 51:05.479
I began to wonder
what they really had against Kurtz.

51:07.022 --> 51:09.233
It wasn't just insanity and murder.

51:10.025 --> 51:12.027
There was enough of that to go around
for everyone.

51:20.744 --> 51:22.788
[Lance] The lady became his mistress...

51:23.831 --> 51:25.457
I mean, he never was hurting for pussy.

51:25.541 --> 51:27.793
-[Chef] Not here
-[soldier laughs]

51:28.335 --> 51:30.963
[Chef] I'm walking through the jungle
gathering mangoes.

51:32.339 --> 51:34.049
I meet Raquel Welch.

51:34.508 --> 51:36.385
[insects chirping]

51:36.760 --> 51:39.221
Make a nice mango cream pudding.

51:41.932 --> 51:44.977
Just, you know,
kind of spread it around on us.

51:46.812 --> 51:48.606
Hey, Captain, I want to get some mangoes.

51:50.024 --> 51:51.525
Just don't go out there by yourself.

51:52.901 --> 51:54.653
You don't want to go
in there alone,

51:56.405 --> 51:58.032
not unless you really know the territory.

51:58.282 --> 52:00.075
Any poisonous snakes around here?

52:00.659 --> 52:03.454
Fuck it.
I'm gonna go eat some mango.

52:11.879 --> 52:12.755
[Willard] Chef.

52:13.547 --> 52:14.465
Yes, sir?

52:14.757 --> 52:16.216
[Willard] How come they call you that?

52:16.550 --> 52:18.052
[Chef] Call me what, sir?

52:18.636 --> 52:20.679
[Willard] Chef.
Because you like mangoes and stuff?

52:20.929 --> 52:22.598
No, sir. I'm a real chef.

52:23.807 --> 52:25.142
I'm a saucier.

52:26.268 --> 52:27.227
[Willard] Saucier?

52:27.936 --> 52:28.812
[Chef] Yes, sir.

52:29.897 --> 52:31.440
See, I come from New Orleans.

52:31.774 --> 52:33.776
I was raised to be a saucier.

52:34.485 --> 52:35.611
A great saucier.

52:36.403 --> 52:37.863
[Willard] What's a saucier?

52:38.030 --> 52:39.907
[Chef] We specialize in sauces.

52:43.661 --> 52:46.080
[Chef] There's got to be
a mango tree here somewhere.

52:53.003 --> 52:57.508
Then I was supposed to go to Paris,
study at the Escoffier school.

52:58.842 --> 53:01.762
Then I got orders for my physical.

53:14.900 --> 53:17.986
Hell, I joined the navy.
Heard they had better food.

53:19.446 --> 53:21.448
Cook school, that did it.

53:21.907 --> 53:23.117
[Willard] Oh, yeah? How's that?

53:23.909 --> 53:25.786
[Chef] Oh, you don't want
to hear about that.

53:28.539 --> 53:31.917
They lined us up in front
of a hundred yards of prime rib.

53:32.751 --> 53:35.295
All of us, you know,
lined up looking at it.

53:36.004 --> 53:38.132
Magnificent meat, really,

53:38.757 --> 53:39.883
beautifully marbled.

53:41.051 --> 53:42.386
Magnifique.

53:43.011 --> 53:45.889
Next thing they're throwing the meat
into these big cauldrons.

53:46.807 --> 53:48.642
All of it. Boiling it.

53:50.144 --> 53:52.354
I looked inside, man,
it was turning gray.

53:54.106 --> 53:55.858
I couldn't fucking believe that one,

53:56.942 --> 53:58.736
that's when I applied
for radioman's school,

53:58.819 --> 54:00.320
but then they gave me the engine ma...

54:10.122 --> 54:13.041
[birds fly from the trees]

54:42.196 --> 54:43.447
What is it?

54:45.949 --> 54:46.867
Charlie?

54:54.208 --> 54:55.250
[grass rustles]

54:56.877 --> 54:58.045
[tiger roars]

54:58.128 --> 54:59.713
-Oh, God!
-[gunshots]

54:59.838 --> 55:00.714
[Chef shouts]

55:01.089 --> 55:02.508
It's a fucking tiger!

55:03.091 --> 55:04.843
Tiger, man! It's a tiger!

55:06.053 --> 55:08.472
[Chief] Battle stations. Lance, up front!
Get on your 60, Clean!

55:08.597 --> 55:09.515
[Clean] Got it, man.

55:09.598 --> 55:10.557
[Chef] Holy shit.

55:10.641 --> 55:11.892
[Willard] Chef, come on!

55:12.976 --> 55:13.936
[Chef] Fucking tiger!

55:14.102 --> 55:16.104
-Captain, come on!
-What's happening?

55:16.230 --> 55:18.398
Go! Let's go!

55:18.524 --> 55:19.566
-[Chef] Tiger!
-[Clean] Man.

55:19.650 --> 55:22.069
[Chef] Chief, you were right!
Never get out of the fucking boat!

55:22.152 --> 55:24.112
-Clean, bring that 60 forward!
-What?

55:24.238 --> 55:26.782
[Chef] Never get out of the boat,
never get out of the boat!

55:26.907 --> 55:28.450
I got to remember,
never get out of the boat!

55:28.534 --> 55:30.369
-[Chief] Clean, on the 60.
-[Chef] Never get out of the boat!

55:30.452 --> 55:32.746
-[machine gun fire]
-[Clean] Get out of here now!

55:32.996 --> 55:34.248
What happened? How many is it?

55:34.456 --> 55:35.874
Fucking tiger!

55:36.124 --> 55:37.751
-What?
-[Chef] Fucking tiger!

55:37.835 --> 55:40.379
-Tiger?
-Yeah! I didn't come here for this!

55:40.504 --> 55:44.049
I'm done with this God damn fucking shit,
man!

55:44.132 --> 55:48.470
You can kiss my ass for the county square
because I'm fucking bugging out!

55:48.554 --> 55:50.514
I didn't come here for this!

55:50.973 --> 55:53.267
I don't fucking need it! I don't want it!

55:53.684 --> 55:57.020
I didn't get on the God damn A-train
for this kind of shit!

55:58.230 --> 56:00.232
All I want to do is fucking cook!

56:00.607 --> 56:02.901
I just want to learn to fucking cook, man!

56:03.151 --> 56:04.528
It's all right. You're all right.

56:04.653 --> 56:06.738
[Clean] For God's sake, man,
what happened, bro?

56:06.905 --> 56:09.116
[Chef laughs manically]

56:09.283 --> 56:10.659
[Lance] It's going to be all right.

56:10.909 --> 56:14.746
[Chef] All right. It's gonna be
all right, it's gonna be all right.

56:14.997 --> 56:18.625
Never get out of the fucking boat.
Never get out of the fucking boat.

56:18.709 --> 56:21.837
Hi, tiger! Bye, tiger! Goodbye!

56:23.630 --> 56:25.382
[Willard] Never get out of the boat.

56:26.425 --> 56:28.385
Absolutely God damn right.

56:30.220 --> 56:31.889
Unless you were going all the way.

56:37.811 --> 56:39.271
Kurtz got off the boat.

56:41.315 --> 56:43.400
He split from the whole fuckin' program.

56:47.070 --> 56:48.447
How did that happen?

56:49.740 --> 56:52.075
What did he see here that first tour?

56:59.041 --> 57:01.168
Thirty-eight fucking years old.

57:02.628 --> 57:06.340
If you joined the green berets, there was
no way you'd ever get above colonel.

57:08.050 --> 57:09.426
Kurtz knew what he was giving up.

57:11.929 --> 57:14.097
The more I read and began to understand,

57:14.890 --> 57:16.141
the more I admired him.

57:17.517 --> 57:19.853
His family and friends couldn't
understand it,

57:20.187 --> 57:21.688
and they couldn't talk him out of it.

57:24.149 --> 57:27.486
He had to apply three times
and he put up with a ton of shit,

57:27.611 --> 57:30.489
but when he threatened to resign,
they gave it to him.

57:34.868 --> 57:38.163
The next youngest guy
in his class was half his age.

57:39.623 --> 57:43.001
They must have thought he was some far-out
old man humping it over that course.

57:44.878 --> 57:47.631
I did it when I was 19
and it damn near wasted me.

57:50.926 --> 57:52.678
A tough motherfucker.

57:54.554 --> 57:55.555
He finished it.

57:58.684 --> 58:00.310
He could have gone for general...

58:02.312 --> 58:04.106
but he went for himself instead.

58:07.567 --> 58:08.819
[Chef] Dear Eva,

58:09.569 --> 58:11.488
Today was really a new one.

58:12.447 --> 58:15.158
Almost got eaten alive by a fucking tiger.

58:17.285 --> 58:19.246
Really un-fucking-believable, you know?

58:19.663 --> 58:22.165
We're taking this guy, Captain Willard,
up the river,

58:22.541 --> 58:23.834
but he hasn't told us yet

58:23.917 --> 58:25.502
-where we're taking him.
-[Clean sings]

58:26.378 --> 58:28.463
♪ Come on, baby, let the good times roll ♪

58:28.630 --> 58:30.590
[Chef] Thought you might have heard by now
from...

58:31.383 --> 58:33.218
[Willard] October 1967.

58:33.719 --> 58:36.304
On special assignment, Kon Tum Province,
II Corps.

58:36.972 --> 58:40.225
Kurtz staged Operation Archangel
with combined local forces,

58:41.059 --> 58:42.728
rated a major success.

58:46.481 --> 58:48.483
He received no official clearance.

58:49.276 --> 58:50.861
He just thought it up and did it.

58:53.196 --> 58:54.281
What balls.

58:56.533 --> 58:59.369
They were going to nail his ass
to the floorboards for that one,

58:59.745 --> 59:03.331
but after the press got a hold of it,
they promoted him to full colonel instead.

59:06.293 --> 59:07.586
Ah, man.

59:08.420 --> 59:12.966
The bullshit piled up so fast in Vietnam,
you needed wings to stay above it.

59:13.842 --> 59:20.015
[drums playing]

59:41.828 --> 59:44.831
This sure enough is a bizarre sight
in the middle of this shit.

59:46.917 --> 59:48.502
[Chief] Expecting us this time?

59:50.670 --> 59:51.546
Damned if I know.

59:53.340 --> 59:55.008
[power tools whir]

59:55.842 --> 1:00:00.013
[man over mic] Anybody hear me?
Hello? Hello? Up, up...

1:00:00.180 --> 1:00:01.098
Jesus.

1:00:01.306 --> 1:00:02.432
[mic screeches]

1:00:07.562 --> 1:00:10.857
[distant Soldier] Get ready.
Let's back up into this truck. What?

1:00:11.024 --> 1:00:13.610
Yeah, we got to get all this stuff up
and off the truck.

1:00:14.319 --> 1:00:16.947
[tools clanging]

1:00:19.658 --> 1:00:22.119
[Clean] Hau Phat. You ever been
up here before, Chef?

1:00:22.244 --> 1:00:23.787
[Chef] I bet you could score up here.

1:00:23.870 --> 1:00:29.918
Yo, man. Check out the bikes, man.
Ooh, Yamahas, Suzuki. Yeah!

1:00:30.001 --> 1:00:31.253
[Chef] That's a good one.

1:00:31.336 --> 1:00:34.381
[Clean] Yeah. Sukiyaki. Yeah, man.
This is all...

1:00:39.386 --> 1:00:41.555
-This must be the guy.
-Right over there.

1:00:47.227 --> 1:00:50.230
[drums playing]

1:00:51.982 --> 1:00:53.984
Three drums of diesel fuel, PBR 5--

1:00:54.067 --> 1:00:57.279
Come on, man, move. We don't have time.
One hour, that's all!

1:00:57.362 --> 1:00:59.322
-What do you want?
-Can I get some Panama Red?

1:00:59.823 --> 1:01:01.241
Panama Red? Yeah.

1:01:01.408 --> 1:01:02.701
-I'll get you Panama Red...
-Sergeant.

1:01:04.035 --> 1:01:06.079
-Destination?
-I don't have no destination.

1:01:06.163 --> 1:01:07.831
[soldier] You can't get a God damn thing
without a destination.

1:01:07.914 --> 1:01:09.499
-Sergeant.
-[Clean] I need diesel fuel.

1:01:09.583 --> 1:01:12.169
-[soldier] You got a destination?
-Sorry.

1:01:13.420 --> 1:01:15.297
Hey, Sarge, sorry, these guys are with me.

1:01:15.755 --> 1:01:17.132
Destination's classified.

1:01:17.215 --> 1:01:19.676
Here are our priority papers from COMSEC
intelligence, II Corps.

1:01:19.759 --> 1:01:22.804
Okay. Right, sir.
Hey, listen, it's a real big night.

1:01:22.888 --> 1:01:24.222
Eight bucks for that Camo.

1:01:24.848 --> 1:01:25.724
