[Chef] Fucking--

1:19:17.503 --> 1:19:20.005
Chef! She's moving behind you!
Check her out!

1:19:20.214 --> 1:19:21.674
[Chef] All right. All right.

1:19:21.966 --> 1:19:24.051
Come on, Clean. Give me a hand.

1:19:24.260 --> 1:19:25.344
Clean, give him a hand.

1:19:25.427 --> 1:19:26.512
[Chef] Fucking...

1:19:27.054 --> 1:19:28.973
[Chief] Hey, take it easy.
Take it easy.

1:19:29.723 --> 1:19:32.393
Slow down and take it easy.
Calm down.

1:19:32.643 --> 1:19:34.353
[Clean] Wait a minute, Chef,
bring her up here.

1:19:34.478 --> 1:19:36.605
-[Chief] Is she breathing, chef?
-[Chef] She's hurt.

1:19:37.439 --> 1:19:38.440
She's bleeding.

1:19:38.607 --> 1:19:40.693
Bring her on board.
We're taking her to an ARVIN

1:19:41.485 --> 1:19:42.695
What are you talking about?

1:19:42.987 --> 1:19:45.990
We're taking her to some friendlies,
Captain. She's wounded. She's not dead.

1:19:46.573 --> 1:19:47.700
Get out of there, Chef.

1:19:47.783 --> 1:19:49.118
-[Phillips] The book says, Captain--
-[gunshot]

1:19:49.368 --> 1:19:50.244
[Chef screams]

1:19:56.417 --> 1:19:58.711
[Chef cries]

1:19:59.753 --> 1:20:02.089
Fuck you. Fuck them.

1:20:02.589 --> 1:20:04.550
I told you not to stop. Now, let's go.

1:20:05.467 --> 1:20:07.261
[bird caws]

1:21:05.861 --> 1:21:08.572
[Willard] It was a way we had over here
of living with ourselves.

1:21:09.948 --> 1:21:12.868
We'd cut them in half with a machine gun
and give them a band-aid.

1:21:15.579 --> 1:21:16.580
It was a lie.

1:21:17.915 --> 1:21:19.458
And the more I saw of them,

1:21:20.626 --> 1:21:22.419
the more I hated lies.

1:21:24.838 --> 1:21:27.716
Those boys were never gonna look
at me the same way again,

1:21:29.551 --> 1:21:33.430
but I felt like I knew one or two things
about Kurtz that weren't in the dossier.

1:21:35.891 --> 1:21:38.394
[explosion]

1:21:39.478 --> 1:21:43.023
Do Lung bridge was the last army outpost
on the Nung River.

1:21:45.067 --> 1:21:46.443
[explosion]

1:21:47.945 --> 1:21:49.738
Beyond it, there was only Kurtz.

1:21:52.282 --> 1:21:53.283
[Chef] Lance.

1:21:53.742 --> 1:21:55.994
Hey, Lance, what do you think?

1:21:56.620 --> 1:21:57.663
It's beautiful.

1:21:58.497 --> 1:22:02.292
Huh? I mean, what's the matter with you?
You're acting kind of weird.

1:22:03.544 --> 1:22:06.130
Hey, you know that last tab
of acid I was saving?

1:22:06.422 --> 1:22:07.339
Yeah.

1:22:08.048 --> 1:22:08.966
[Lance] I dropped it.

1:22:09.133 --> 1:22:10.134
[Chef] You dropped acid?

1:22:10.551 --> 1:22:11.760
Far out.

1:22:13.929 --> 1:22:15.639
[soldier] Hey, friendly!

1:22:15.722 --> 1:22:17.307
[soldiers] Friendly! Friendly!

1:22:18.809 --> 1:22:22.354
[soldiers shouting]

1:22:23.564 --> 1:22:26.900
[soldier] Take me home! God damn it!

1:22:26.984 --> 1:22:29.945
Fucking shore police! Shit!
You want to die?

1:22:30.070 --> 1:22:31.864
[soldier] Take me home!

1:22:32.448 --> 1:22:34.450
[soldier 2] Motherfuckers!

1:22:34.533 --> 1:22:36.201
[soldier 3] Hey! You fucking police!

1:22:36.285 --> 1:22:38.912
-[soldier 4] Don't leave me!
-[soldier 5] Fuck you!

1:22:39.079 --> 1:22:41.123
You'll get what you deserve!

1:22:41.874 --> 1:22:44.293
[soldiers shouting]

1:22:49.131 --> 1:22:51.967
[Carlson]
Is there a Captain Willard on board?

1:22:52.050 --> 1:22:52.926
[Willard] Yeah.

1:22:53.010 --> 1:22:54.761
-[Carlson] Captain Willard?
-Yeah, who's that?

1:22:54.928 --> 1:22:57.890
Lieutenant Carlson, sir.
Get that light off me!

1:22:59.641 --> 1:23:02.436
I was sent here from Nha Trang with these
three days ago, sir.

1:23:02.603 --> 1:23:05.397
Expected you here a little sooner.
This is mail for the boat.

1:23:06.273 --> 1:23:08.025
You don't know how happy
this makes me, sir.

1:23:08.150 --> 1:23:09.902
-Why?
-Now I can get out of here,

1:23:09.985 --> 1:23:11.195
if I can find a way.

1:23:13.071 --> 1:23:15.199
[explosion]

1:23:15.491 --> 1:23:18.118
You're in the asshole of the world,
Captain!

1:23:23.081 --> 1:23:24.374
Captain, where you going?

1:23:24.708 --> 1:23:27.419
I gotta find somebody.
I need some information.

1:23:29.046 --> 1:23:30.756
Pick me up the other side of the bridge.

1:23:30.881 --> 1:23:32.799
Somebody go with him. Chef.

1:23:33.091 --> 1:23:33.967
[Lance] I'll go.

1:23:34.968 --> 1:23:36.845
-I want to go.
-[explosion]

1:23:39.932 --> 1:23:41.266
[machine gun fire]

1:23:41.475 --> 1:23:42.935
[soldiers shouting]

1:23:49.566 --> 1:23:52.152
[soldier over speakerphone]
Contact, will you get your ass in gear?

1:23:54.321 --> 1:23:57.157
[indistinct speakerphone announcement]

1:23:57.991 --> 1:24:00.369
[distorted circus music plays]

1:24:01.912 --> 1:24:02.955
[explosion]

1:24:15.092 --> 1:24:17.094
[explosions]

1:24:17.219 --> 1:24:18.929
[laser gun noises]

1:24:19.972 --> 1:24:21.431
[soldiers screaming]

1:24:28.981 --> 1:24:31.191
[Lance] Man, listen to the music, man.

1:24:31.692 --> 1:24:33.360
[Willard] Where can I find the CO?

1:24:33.443 --> 1:24:35.654
[soldier] You came right to it,
son of a bitch!

1:24:35.737 --> 1:24:38.824
[Willard] Lance! Get down here!

1:24:41.994 --> 1:24:43.954
[Willard] You still got
a commanding officer here?

1:24:44.830 --> 1:24:45.914
[soldier] Beverly Hills.

1:24:46.206 --> 1:24:47.124
[Willard] What?

1:24:47.457 --> 1:24:48.750
[soldier] Straight up the road,

1:24:48.875 --> 1:24:52.004
there's a concrete fucking bunker
called Beverly Hills.

1:24:52.421 --> 1:24:54.840
Where the fuck else
do you think it would be?

1:24:54.965 --> 1:24:57.009
[soldier 2] I don't want to die.

1:25:00.887 --> 1:25:04.349
[rock music playing]

1:25:04.516 --> 1:25:05.601
[gunshots]

1:25:06.143 --> 1:25:08.604
[machine gun fire]

1:25:09.146 --> 1:25:10.105
[explosion]

1:25:16.945 --> 1:25:18.155
[explosion]

1:25:25.829 --> 1:25:28.290
[machine gun fire]

1:25:28.415 --> 1:25:29.875
[explosion]

1:25:30.292 --> 1:25:32.169
[soldier 3] God damn it!
You stepped in my face.

1:25:32.336 --> 1:25:34.963
-[Lance] Thought you were dead.
-[soldier 3] You thought wrong, damn it.

1:25:36.465 --> 1:25:38.800
[machine gun fire]

1:25:39.009 --> 1:25:41.094
[gunner] I told you to stop
fucking with me! Didn't I?

1:25:41.178 --> 1:25:42.596
Think you're so bad, huh, nigga?

1:25:42.804 --> 1:25:44.931
-[machine gun fire]
-What are you shooting at, soldier?

1:25:45.015 --> 1:25:47.142
Gooks, man. What the fuck
do you think I'm shootin' at?

1:25:47.476 --> 1:25:50.145
I’m sorry, sir.
There are gooks out there by the wire.

1:25:50.437 --> 1:25:51.772
But I think I killed them all.

1:25:51.938 --> 1:25:53.982
You ain't shot shit, man.
Listen.

1:25:54.149 --> 1:25:55.359
[Viet Cong yelling]

1:25:55.609 --> 1:25:58.570
[gunner] Oh, shit. He's trying to call
his friends, man. Send up a flare.

1:25:58.945 --> 1:26:00.405
[flare fires]

1:26:04.910 --> 1:26:07.496
[machine gun fire]

1:26:07.579 --> 1:26:10.040
[gunner] You think you so bad, nigga?
You think you bad, huh?

1:26:10.207 --> 1:26:13.251
They're all dead, stupid.
There's one alive underneath them bodies.

1:26:14.211 --> 1:26:15.921
Who's the commanding officer here?

1:26:16.546 --> 1:26:17.589
Ain't you?

1:26:18.298 --> 1:26:19.174
[gunshot]

1:26:20.384 --> 1:26:22.636
-You think you so bad, huh?
-[machine gun fire]

1:26:22.719 --> 1:26:25.847
I got something for your ass now, nigga!
I got something for you now! [laughs]

1:26:28.225 --> 1:26:29.935
[spotter] He's underneath the bodies,
man.

1:26:30.102 --> 1:26:31.269
[explosion]

1:26:33.271 --> 1:26:35.482
Go get the roach, man.
Go get the roach, nigga!

1:26:36.066 --> 1:26:38.110
-[spotter] I'll get the roach.
-[gunner] Go get him.

1:26:38.860 --> 1:26:41.488
[rock music playing]

1:26:42.114 --> 1:26:43.115
[spotter] Roach.

1:26:43.490 --> 1:26:44.574
Roach.

1:26:44.908 --> 1:26:45.826
Roach.

1:26:46.576 --> 1:26:48.745
You got slopes on the wire, man
You hear 'em?

1:26:49.204 --> 1:26:50.122
Lance!

1:26:50.330 --> 1:26:51.498
[spotter] Do you hear them?

1:26:52.666 --> 1:26:56.253
[Viet Cong yelling]

1:26:56.503 --> 1:26:57.504
Well, bust him.

1:27:00.841 --> 1:27:03.301
[Viet Cong] Hey, GIs! Fuck you!

1:27:07.514 --> 1:27:08.390
[music stops]

1:27:09.224 --> 1:27:10.684
[distant explosions]

1:27:10.851 --> 1:27:13.061
[Viet Cong yelling]

1:27:13.186 --> 1:27:15.147
[gunner] You hear him out there
on the wire, man?

1:27:16.273 --> 1:27:17.399
Yeah.

1:27:18.024 --> 1:27:19.818
[Viet Cong] I'll kill you, GIs!

1:27:20.152 --> 1:27:21.153
You need a flare?

1:27:21.653 --> 1:27:22.529
[gunshots]

1:27:22.988 --> 1:27:23.864
No.

1:27:25.407 --> 1:27:26.783
He's close, man.

1:27:27.951 --> 1:27:29.619
He's real close.

1:27:37.586 --> 1:27:40.714
[Viet Cong yelling]

1:27:51.975 --> 1:27:54.019
[Viet Cong] GIs, fuck you!

1:27:55.479 --> 1:27:56.938
GIs!

1:27:57.606 --> 1:27:59.941
-GIs! Fuck y--
-[explosion]

1:28:04.321 --> 1:28:05.447
Motherfucker.

1:28:06.907 --> 1:28:07.824
[Willard] Hey, soldier.

1:28:12.788 --> 1:28:14.456
Do you know who's in command here?

1:28:17.459 --> 1:28:18.335
Yeah.

1:28:23.715 --> 1:28:24.800
[distant gunshots]

1:28:29.471 --> 1:28:30.472
[explosion]

1:28:30.597 --> 1:28:32.224
[soldier screaming]

1:28:32.849 --> 1:28:35.018
Holy shit.

1:28:35.185 --> 1:28:36.645
[explosion]

1:28:40.148 --> 1:28:42.984
Chief, two guys just got blown off that
bridge.

1:28:43.109 --> 1:28:45.362
You hang on, man. You're going to be okay.

1:28:48.824 --> 1:28:49.699
[explosion]

1:28:49.991 --> 1:28:50.951
[Clean] What's that?

1:28:51.034 --> 1:28:51.952
[Chef] Mail, man.

1:28:52.035 --> 1:28:54.037
Later on the mail. Watch them trees.

1:28:56.581 --> 1:28:58.917
There's no diesel fuel,
but I picked up some ammo.

1:28:59.501 --> 1:29:00.502
Let's move out.

1:29:01.419 --> 1:29:02.879
Did you find the CO, Captain?

1:29:02.963 --> 1:29:04.631
[Willard] There's no fucking CO here.

1:29:07.217 --> 1:29:08.718
Let's just get going.

1:29:09.386 --> 1:29:10.387
Which way, Captain?

1:29:16.685 --> 1:29:18.019
You know which way, Chief.

1:29:19.729 --> 1:29:21.189
You're on your own, Captain.

1:29:23.149 --> 1:29:24.317
Still want to go on?

1:29:25.151 --> 1:29:28.780
Like this bridge, we build it every night,
Charlie blows it right back up again.

1:29:29.197 --> 1:29:31.449
Just so the generals can say
the road's open.

1:29:32.409 --> 1:29:33.285
Think about it.

1:29:36.872 --> 1:29:38.790
-Who cares?
-Just get us upriver!

1:29:44.004 --> 1:29:46.089
Chef. On the bow.

1:29:47.591 --> 1:29:48.758
Stand by, Clean.

1:29:48.842 --> 1:29:49.718
[Chef] Let's go!

1:29:57.851 --> 1:30:00.896
[explosions]

1:30:04.149 --> 1:30:05.483
[explosion]

1:30:12.115 --> 1:30:13.116
[explosion]

1:30:46.274 --> 1:30:47.525
[Clean] Whose package is that?

1:30:47.776 --> 1:30:49.235
Shit, you got another one, Clean.

1:30:49.402 --> 1:30:51.613
No shit. Wait a minute, is that it?

1:30:52.322 --> 1:30:54.240
That's it for you. Lance!

1:30:54.783 --> 1:30:56.826
Mr. L.B. Johnson. There you go.

1:30:58.662 --> 1:31:01.289
Far out, man. All right!
I've been waiting for this one.

1:31:02.040 --> 1:31:05.001
[Chef] I got another one.
I got a box from Eva.

1:31:05.335 --> 1:31:10.090
[Lance] "Lance, I'm fine.
Sue and I went tripping in Disney Land.

1:31:10.465 --> 1:31:11.716
Sue skinned her knee."

1:31:12.008 --> 1:31:13.969
[Chef]
Man, I I'm gonna get back to Antoine's.

1:31:14.052 --> 1:31:16.680
[Lance] Course I remember the time,
how could I fucking forget, man?

1:31:16.763 --> 1:31:17.847
Beautiful!

1:31:18.932 --> 1:31:21.518
"There could never be
a place like Disneyland, or could there?

1:31:21.601 --> 1:31:22.560
Let me know."

1:31:22.852 --> 1:31:26.189
Jim, it's here. It really is here.

1:31:30.735 --> 1:31:33.279
[Willard] "There has been
a new development regarding your mission

1:31:33.363 --> 1:31:35.115
which we must now communicate to you.

1:31:35.699 --> 1:31:38.952
Months ago, a man was ordered on a
mission which was identical to yours.

1:31:40.036 --> 1:31:43.331
We have reason to believe that he is
now operating with Colonel Kurtz.

1:31:45.458 --> 1:31:48.336
Saigon was carrying him MIA
for his family's sake,

1:31:49.295 --> 1:31:50.630
but they assumed he was dead.

1:31:51.673 --> 1:31:54.342
Then they intercepted a letter
he tried to send to his wife."

1:31:59.055 --> 1:32:00.181
Captain Richard Colby.

1:32:03.059 --> 1:32:04.185
He was with Kurtz.

1:32:04.310 --> 1:32:05.311
[Lance] Look at this guy!

1:32:06.146 --> 1:32:07.397
Disneyland.

1:32:08.356 --> 1:32:10.525
Fuck, man, this is better than Disneyland.

1:32:11.234 --> 1:32:15.822
[Chef] "Charles Miller Manson ordered
the slaughter of all in the home anyway

1:32:15.947 --> 1:32:17.323
as a symbol of protest."

1:32:17.449 --> 1:32:19.534
-That's really weird, ain't it?
-[flare popping]

1:32:20.160 --> 1:32:23.329
-Purple haze. Look.
-[Chief] Hey, Lance, put away that smoke.

1:32:23.413 --> 1:32:24.831
[Clean] I got a tape from my mom.

1:32:24.914 --> 1:32:29.127
Chief, rainbow reality, man.
Hey, chief, get a good whiff.

1:32:29.586 --> 1:32:32.005
[Chef] Eva can't picture me in Vietnam.

1:32:33.173 --> 1:32:37.010
She pictures me at home
having a beer, watching TV. [laughs]

1:32:38.011 --> 1:32:39.012
Hey, Lance, man.

1:32:39.471 --> 1:32:41.139
Ooh! Hot potato! Hot potato!

1:32:42.098 --> 1:32:44.476
[Clean's mother on tape]
I'm so glad you decided to join the...

1:32:44.684 --> 1:32:47.353
[Chef] Eva's not sure she could have
a relationship with me, you know.

1:32:47.479 --> 1:32:50.607
[laughs] Here I am,
13,000 fucking miles away,

1:32:50.690 --> 1:32:53.109
trying to keep a relationship up
with my ass.

1:32:54.027 --> 1:32:55.987
[Clean's mother]
...that's much more than I can say

1:32:56.071 --> 1:32:57.405
for some of your friends.

1:32:57.989 --> 1:32:59.824
If this tape is any good,

1:33:00.116 --> 1:33:02.702
I will have Dad and the family
send you a tape

1:33:02.786 --> 1:33:04.204
-...of their own.
-[Chef] Hey, Lance.

1:33:04.537 --> 1:33:09.375
[gunshots]

1:33:17.092 --> 1:33:18.843
[machine gun fire]

1:33:20.053 --> 1:33:21.346
[bullets hitting the boat]

1:33:21.429 --> 1:33:23.389
[Lance screaming]

1:33:23.681 --> 1:33:24.808
There! Over there!

1:33:25.558 --> 1:33:26.684
[explosion]

1:33:26.768 --> 1:33:27.685
[Chef] Damn it!

1:33:27.852 --> 1:33:29.062
[Lance] Motherfucker!

1:33:29.354 --> 1:33:31.397
-[Lance screaming]
-[machine gun fire]

1:33:31.731 --> 1:33:34.859
-[machine gun fire]
-[bullets hitting the boat]

1:33:37.112 --> 1:33:38.488
[shouting]

1:33:38.696 --> 1:33:40.281
[machine gun fire]

1:33:42.909 --> 1:33:44.369
[screaming]

1:33:50.542 --> 1:33:53.545
Chef! Chef! Check out Clean!

1:33:53.711 --> 1:33:55.713
Captain, he's hit, he's hit!
Clean's hit!

1:33:56.172 --> 1:33:57.882
Where'd the dog go?

1:33:58.133 --> 1:34:00.927
[Chief] Lance! Lance, check out Clean!

1:34:01.344 --> 1:34:04.305
Where's the dog?
We got to go back and get the dog!

1:34:04.597 --> 1:34:05.640
Hey, Clean!

1:34:05.723 --> 1:34:08.434
[Clean's mother]
It's always been my dream to have a boy...

1:34:08.518 --> 1:34:09.853
Hey, Bubber!

1:34:10.436 --> 1:34:12.981
Bubber, you can't die, you fucker!

1:34:14.691 --> 1:34:16.151
Hey, Bubber!
[cries]

1:34:16.401 --> 1:34:20.905
[Clean's mother] ...I'm hoping that
pretty soon, not too soon,

1:34:21.447 --> 1:34:25.660
but pretty soon, I'll have a lot
of grandchildren to love and spoil.

1:34:26.411 --> 1:34:30.623
Then when your wife gets them back,
she'll be mad with me. Ha ha ha.

1:34:31.916 --> 1:34:37.213
Even Aunt Jessie and Mama will come
to celebrate your coming home.

1:34:37.755 --> 1:34:41.050
Granny and Dad are trying to get
enough money to get you a car,

1:34:41.426 --> 1:34:44.637
but don't tell them
because that's our secret.

1:34:46.264 --> 1:34:48.516
Anyhow, do the right thing,

1:34:49.225 --> 1:34:50.852
stay out of the way of the bullets,

1:34:51.603 --> 1:34:55.315
and bring your heinie home
all in one piece,

1:34:55.815 --> 1:34:57.400
because we love you very much.

1:34:58.234 --> 1:34:59.652
Love, Mom.

1:35:08.286 --> 1:35:11.456
[Chief crying]
You were so young.

1:35:49.786 --> 1:35:51.371
[bird caws]

1:36:36.958 --> 1:36:39.210
[distant shouting]

1:36:42.964 --> 1:36:44.424
[distant shouting]

1:36:48.136 --> 1:36:50.596
[Chief] Can't see nothing.
We're stopping.

1:36:51.139 --> 1:36:53.349
[Willard] You're not authorized
to stop this boat, Chief.

1:36:53.558 --> 1:36:56.769
[Chief] I said I can't see a thing,
Captain. I'm stopping this boat.

1:36:57.145 --> 1:36:58.771
I ain't risking no more lives.

1:36:58.896 --> 1:37:01.357
[Willard] I'm in command here,
God damn it. You'll do what I say.

1:37:01.733 --> 1:37:03.526
[howling noise]

1:37:03.943 --> 1:37:05.320
[Chief] You see anything, Chef?

1:37:05.611 --> 1:37:07.030
[howling noise]

1:37:08.072 --> 1:37:10.158
Why don't they fucking attack, man?

1:37:10.783 --> 1:37:12.744
[Lance howling]

1:37:13.953 --> 1:37:16.956
[Lance howling]

1:37:29.552 --> 1:37:31.137
[Chef] Watch it over here, Chief!

1:37:32.889 --> 1:37:34.057
Gotta stoop.

1:37:36.559 --> 1:37:38.144
Lance, on the 50s.

1:37:39.145 --> 1:37:40.188
[Willard] He was close.

1:37:42.857 --> 1:37:44.525
He was real close.

1:37:46.986 --> 1:37:48.946
I couldn't see him yet,
but I could feel him,

1:37:49.906 --> 1:37:51.783
as if the boat were being sucked upriver

1:37:51.866 --> 1:37:54.077
and the water was flowing
back into the jungle.

1:37:57.330 --> 1:37:58.873
Whatever was going to happen,

1:37:59.832 --> 1:38:02.710
it wouldn't be the way they called it
back in Nha Trang.

1:38:07.423 --> 1:38:08.466
[arrows whistling]

1:38:08.549 --> 1:38:09.425
Arrows!

1:38:09.926 --> 1:38:11.427
Fire!

1:38:11.511 --> 1:38:12.553
[arrows whistling]

1:38:13.346 --> 1:38:15.264
Chef, open up fire!

1:38:15.765 --> 1:38:17.392
[arrows whistling]

1:38:19.769 --> 1:38:21.854
-Lance, fire!
-[machine gun fire]

1:38:24.941 --> 1:38:26.609
[arrows whistling]

1:38:27.151 --> 1:38:28.569
[machine gun fire]

1:38:29.445 --> 1:38:30.488
Chef!

1:38:30.822 --> 1:38:32.615
Chef, it's okay! Quit firing!

1:38:32.698 --> 1:38:35.076
-[machine gun fire]
-They're just little toy arrows.

1:38:35.159 --> 1:38:37.161
-Cut it out! Quiet!
-[machine gun fire]

1:38:37.286 --> 1:38:39.539
Chief, tell them to hold their fire!

1:38:39.664 --> 1:38:42.333
They're just little sticks,
they're just trying to scare us.

1:38:42.458 --> 1:38:44.836
-[machine gun fire]
-Quiet!

1:38:45.086 --> 1:38:47.672
You got us into this mess
and now you can't get us out,

1:38:47.755 --> 1:38:49.841
because you don't know where the hell
you going, do ya?

1:38:50.425 --> 1:38:51.342
Do ya?

1:38:52.343 --> 1:38:55.179
-[machine gun fire]
-You son of a bitch! You bastard!

1:38:55.972 --> 1:38:57.348
[machine gun fire]

1:38:57.473 --> 1:38:59.058
Fire! Fire! Fire!

1:38:59.725 --> 1:39:02.019
-[machine gun fire]
-You savage, come and get it!

1:39:02.103 --> 1:39:03.312
You son of a bitches!!

1:39:04.605 --> 1:39:06.524
-[Chef screaming]
-[machine gun fire]

1:39:08.818 --> 1:39:10.111
[Chief groans]

1:39:24.083 --> 1:39:25.168
A spear?

1:39:51.235 --> 1:39:52.111
[Chief groans]

1:39:52.945 --> 1:39:54.030
[Willard groans]

1:39:58.743 --> 1:39:59.702
[Willard groans]

1:40:00.703 --> 1:40:01.787
[Chief gasps]

1:40:05.082 --> 1:40:06.125
[Willard pants]

1:40:45.331 --> 1:40:47.583
[Willard] My mission is to make it
up into Cambodia.

1:40:48.668 --> 1:40:51.045
There's a Green Beret colonel up there
who's gone insane.

1:40:51.128 --> 1:40:52.380
I'm supposed to kill him.

1:40:54.507 --> 1:40:55.967
That's fucking typical.

1:40:56.467 --> 1:40:59.262
Shit! Fucking Vietnam mission.

1:40:59.762 --> 1:41:02.932
I'm short, and we got to go up there
so you can kill one of our own guys.

1:41:03.641 --> 1:41:04.934
That's fucking great!

1:41:05.268 --> 1:41:07.061
That's just fucking great, man!

1:41:08.396 --> 1:41:11.274
Shit! That's fucking crazy!

1:41:11.691 --> 1:41:14.527
I mean, I thought you were going in
to blow up a bridge

1:41:14.860 --> 1:41:17.613
or some fucking railroad tracks
or something.

1:41:18.531 --> 1:41:19.407
Sorry.

1:41:19.574 --> 1:41:22.577
No. No, wait, wait.
We'll go together on the boat.

1:41:22.785 --> 1:41:23.744
We'll go with you.

1:41:24.161 --> 1:41:25.997
We'll go up there, but on the boat.

1:41:27.123 --> 1:41:28.040
Okay?

1:42:34.774 --> 1:42:36.942
[Willard] Part of me was afraid
of what I would find

1:42:37.026 --> 1:42:38.736
and what I would do when I got there.

1:42:41.864 --> 1:42:43.157
I knew the risks...

1:42:44.784 --> 1:42:46.243
or imagined I knew.

1:42:48.913 --> 1:42:50.498
But the thing I felt the most,

1:42:51.540 --> 1:42:53.209
much stronger than fear,

1:42:54.669 --> 1:42:56.796
was the desire to confront him.

1:44:09.410 --> 1:44:10.745
Just keep moving.

1:44:11.537 --> 1:44:14.999
Lance, keep your hands away from the guns.

1:45:39.625 --> 1:45:41.752
[tin drums playing]

1:45:41.877 --> 1:45:43.754
[photographer]
It's all right! It's all right!

1:45:43.838 --> 1:45:45.464
It's all been approved!

1:45:46.131 --> 1:45:47.550
I ain't coming in there!

1:45:48.008 --> 1:45:49.385
Them bastards attacked us!

1:45:50.094 --> 1:45:52.471
[photographer]
Come on! Zap them with your siren, man!

1:45:52.555 --> 1:45:54.056
Zap them with your siren!

1:45:56.016 --> 1:46:00.271
[siren sounds]

1:46:04.483 --> 1:46:06.694
There's mines over there
and mines over there, too!

1:46:06.861 --> 1:46:09.238
And watch out. Those God damn monkeys bite
you, I'll tell you.

1:46:09.864 --> 1:46:12.491
Wow. That's a pretty one.
Move it right in toward me.

1:46:13.659 --> 1:46:17.621
I'm an American.
Yeah! I'm an American civilian. Hi, Yanks.

1:46:18.497 --> 1:46:19.915
Hi. American.

1:46:20.457 --> 1:46:22.001
American civilian. It's all right.

1:46:22.793 --> 1:46:25.379
And you've got the cigarettes
and that's what I've been dreaming of.

1:46:26.714 --> 1:46:27.590
Chef...

1:46:28.465 --> 1:46:29.425
Who are you?

1:46:30.384 --> 1:46:34.221
Who are you? [laughs]

1:46:35.389 --> 1:46:37.057
I'm a photojournalist.

1:46:37.766 --> 1:46:39.560
I've covered the war since '64.

1:46:40.144 --> 1:46:42.146
I've been in Laos, Cambodia, Nam.

1:46:43.480 --> 1:46:45.065
A-phew-wee!

1:46:45.691 --> 1:46:46.859
Phew-wee, baby!

1:46:47.526 --> 1:46:50.696
I'll tell you one thing.
This boat is a mess, man. Woo.

1:46:51.071 --> 1:46:52.323
Who are all these people?

1:46:52.573 --> 1:46:55.200
Yeah, well,
they think you've come to, uh...

1:46:56.619 --> 1:46:58.996
To take him away
and I hope that isn't true.

1:46:59.830 --> 1:47:00.873
Take who away?

1:47:03.042 --> 1:47:03.959
Him!

1:47:04.793 --> 1:47:05.878
Colonel Kurtz.

1:47:06.712 --> 1:47:09.673
These are all his children,
man, as far as you can see.

1:47:10.758 --> 1:47:13.469
Hell, man, out here,
we're all his children.

1:47:14.345 --> 1:47:17.640
Could we, uh, talk to Colonel Kurtz?

1:47:18.098 --> 1:47:21.352
Hey, man, you don't talk to the colonel.

1:47:22.436 --> 1:47:23.938
Well-- Well, you listen to him.

1:47:24.480 --> 1:47:27.316
Uh... the man's enlarged my mind.

1:47:27.942 --> 1:47:31.278
He's a poet-warrior in a classic sense.

1:47:31.862 --> 1:47:34.657
I mean, sometimes,
you'll say hello to him, right,

1:47:34.782 --> 1:47:36.283
and he'll just walk right by you.

1:47:36.408 --> 1:47:38.827
He won't even notice you
and then suddenly he'll grab you,

1:47:38.911 --> 1:47:41.121
and he'll-- He'll throw you in a corner,
and he'll say,

1:47:41.246 --> 1:47:43.290
"Do you know that "if"
is the middle word in life?"

1:47:43.374 --> 1:47:45.501
If you can keep your head
when all about you are losing theirs

1:47:45.584 --> 1:47:47.628
and blaming it on you, if you can
trust yourself when all men doubt you,"

1:47:47.711 --> 1:47:51.966
I mean, I know I can't-- I'm a little man.
I'ma little man. He's a great man.

1:47:52.257 --> 1:47:55.260
Uh, I should have been
a pair of ragged claws,

1:47:55.469 --> 1:47:58.097
uh, scuttling across floors
of silent seas.

1:47:58.180 --> 1:47:59.515
-I mean, uh--
-Stay with the boat.

1:47:59.682 --> 1:48:02.184
Don't go any-- Don't go without me, okay?

1:48:02.851 --> 1:48:04.144
I want to get a picture.

1:48:06.814 --> 1:48:09.441
He can be terrible,
and he can be mean...

1:48:09.566 --> 1:48:11.443
-[camera clicks]
-...and he can be right.

1:48:12.236 --> 1:48:13.529
He's fighting the war.

1:48:14.405 --> 1:48:15.656
He's a great man.

1:48:16.115 --> 1:48:17.032
[camera clicks]

1:48:17.366 --> 1:48:19.410
[laughs] I mean...

1:48:22.997 --> 1:48:24.623
I wish I had words, man.

1:48:25.541 --> 1:48:26.500
I wish I had words.

1:48:26.667 --> 1:48:29.545
I can tell you something,
like the other day, he wanted to kill me.

1:48:29.837 --> 1:48:30.879
Something like that.

1:48:31.130 --> 1:48:32.423
Why did he want to kill you?

1:48:32.589 --> 1:48:34.216
[laughs]
Because I took his picture.

1:48:35.342 --> 1:48:37.469
He said, "If you take my picture again,

1:48:39.013 --> 1:48:39.930
I'm going to kill you."

1:48:41.348 --> 1:48:42.725
And he meant it.

1:48:45.394 --> 1:48:47.771
So you just lay cool, play it cool.

1:48:48.063 --> 1:48:49.398
Lay back, dig it?

1:48:49.982 --> 1:48:51.859
He gets friendly again. He really does.

1:48:53.277 --> 1:48:55.988
But, uh, you don't--
You don't judge the colonel.

1:48:56.822 --> 1:48:58.782
You don't judge the colonel
like an ordinary man.

1:48:59.324 --> 1:49:01.452
[birds cawing]

1:49:04.413 --> 1:49:05.372
[photographer whistles]

1:49:05.539 --> 1:49:08.792
Okay, watch it now.
These are Americans! Americans!

1:49:09.209 --> 1:49:10.878
Feel the vibe of this place.

1:49:11.420 --> 1:49:12.546
Let me take your picture.

1:49:13.005 --> 1:49:15.966
Hey, could you-- Hello?
Hello? Could you hold it a minute?

1:49:18.844 --> 1:49:21.221
[camera shutter clicks repeatedly]

1:49:38.989 --> 1:49:40.157
[Willard] Colby.

1:49:56.507 --> 1:49:57.633
[photographer] The heads...

1:49:58.884 --> 1:50:00.385
You're looking at the heads.

1:50:00.803 --> 1:50:04.014
Hey, sometimes he goes too far.

1:50:05.057 --> 1:50:06.433
He's the first one to admit it.

1:50:07.851 --> 1:50:08.936
[Chef] He's gone crazy.

1:50:09.061 --> 1:50:10.187
Wrong! Wrong!

1:50:12.189 --> 1:50:14.900
If you could have heard the man
just two days ago...

1:50:15.025 --> 1:50:16.944
If you could have heard him then, God...

1:50:17.903 --> 1:50:19.655
You're gonna call him crazy?

1:50:20.405 --> 1:50:21.281
Fuckin' A.

1:50:22.950 --> 1:50:24.451
I just want to talk to him.

1:50:26.870 --> 1:50:28.497
Well, man, he's gone away.

1:50:30.207 --> 1:50:32.793
He's gone away, disappeared
out in the jungle with his people.

1:50:32.876 --> 1:50:33.794
I'll wait for him.

1:50:33.877 --> 1:50:35.754
He feels comfortable with his people.

1:50:36.505 --> 1:50:38.382
He forgets himself with his people.

1:50:40.551 --> 1:50:41.885
He forgets himself.

1:50:42.136 --> 1:50:45.013
Captain.
Maybe we should wait back at the boat.

1:50:46.348 --> 1:50:47.891
-I think--
-[Willard] Okay, Chef.

1:50:48.308 --> 1:50:50.060
We'll go back to the boat for a while.

1:50:50.477 --> 1:50:52.813
Yeah. Stay with Lance.

1:51:03.157 --> 1:51:07.161
[chopping tree]

1:51:14.585 --> 1:51:15.586
[splash]

1:51:16.170 --> 1:51:18.547
[Chef]
This colonel guy, he's wacko, man.

1:51:18.630 --> 1:51:20.841
He's worse than crazy, he's evil.

1:51:21.800 --> 1:51:24.094
I mean, that's what the man's got
set up here, man,

1:51:24.178 --> 1:51:26.471
it's fucking pagan idolatry!
Look around you.

1:51:27.890 --> 1:51:29.183
Shit, he's loco.

1:51:29.516 --> 1:51:30.684
[Willard] Then you'll help me?

1:51:31.143 --> 1:51:34.396
[Chef] Help you? Fuckin' A, I'll help you.
I'll do anything to get out of this joint.

1:51:35.898 --> 1:51:37.566
We could blow
all them assholes away.

1:51:37.691 --> 1:51:39.902
They're so fucking spaced out,
they wouldn't even know it.

1:51:41.195 --> 1:51:45.741
I ain't afraid of all them fucking skulls
and altars and shit.

1:51:47.784 --> 1:51:51.455
I used to think if I died
in an evil place,

1:51:51.997 --> 1:51:54.166
then my soul wouldn't be able
to make it to heaven.

1:51:55.125 --> 1:51:56.251
But now...

1:51:56.793 --> 1:51:58.045
Fuck.

1:51:59.838 --> 1:52:02.507
I mean, I don't care where it goes
as long as it ain't here.

1:52:03.091 --> 1:52:04.426
So what do you want to do?

1:52:05.010 --> 1:52:06.511
-I'll kill the fuck.
-[Willard] No, no.

1:52:06.803 --> 1:52:07.721
Get out of here.

1:52:07.804 --> 1:52:09.723
[Willard]
I'm going to need you to wait here, Chef.

1:52:10.307 --> 1:52:13.769
I'll go up with Lance, scrounge around,
check the place out,

1:52:14.436 --> 1:52:16.647
see if I can find the colonel. Okay?

1:52:17.898 --> 1:52:19.858
[Chef] Well, what do you want me to do?

1:52:19.983 --> 1:52:20.984
Damn it.

1:52:21.193 --> 1:52:23.195
Here. Here, take the radio,

1:52:24.613 --> 1:52:27.574
and if I don't get back by 22:00 hours...

1:52:30.452 --> 1:52:31.662
you'll call in the air strike.

1:52:34.164 --> 1:52:35.374
[Chef] Air strike?

1:52:37.626 --> 1:52:42.339
The code is Almighty,
coordinates 0-niner-2-6-4-7-1-2.

1:52:43.382 --> 1:52:44.508
It's all in there.

1:52:46.134 --> 1:52:49.179
[Chef] 0-niner-2-6-4-7-1-2.

1:52:57.604 --> 1:53:00.816
[Willard] Everything I saw told me
that Kurtz had gone insane.

1:53:05.028 --> 1:53:06.947
The place was full of bodies,

1:53:07.531 --> 1:53:11.326
North Vietnamese, Viet Cong, Cambodians.

1:53:18.834 --> 1:53:21.920
If I was still alive, it was
because he wanted me that way.

1:53:23.171 --> 1:53:26.883
[chanting]

1:53:32.180 --> 1:53:33.098
Hey!

1:53:39.062 --> 1:53:41.315
[Willard shouting]

1:53:47.487 --> 1:53:48.989
[Willard shouting]

1:53:56.288 --> 1:53:58.665
[Willard] It smelled like slow death
in there.

1:54:00.250 --> 1:54:01.335
Malaria.

1:54:02.419 --> 1:54:03.295
Nightmares.

1:54:06.340 --> 1:54:08.342
This was the end of the river, all right.

1:54:17.434 --> 1:54:18.560
[coughing]

1:54:22.564 --> 1:54:24.107
[Kurtz] Where are you from, Willard?

1:54:29.738 --> 1:54:31.365
[Willard] I'm from Ohio, sir.

1:54:33.533 --> 1:54:34.576
[Kurtz coughing]

1:54:37.287 --> 1:54:38.538
[Kurtz] Were you born there?

1:54:39.247 --> 1:54:40.332
[Willard] Yes, sir.

1:54:42.000 --> 1:54:43.251
[Kurtz] Whereabouts?

1:54:44.086 --> 1:54:45.253
[Willard] Toledo, sir.

1:54:52.177 --> 1:54:53.762
How far are you from the river?

1:55:00.852 --> 1:55:02.187
[Willard] The Ohio river, sir?

1:55:03.647 --> 1:55:04.523
[Kurtz] Uh-huh.

1:55:04.981 --> 1:55:06.483
[Willard] About 200 miles.

1:55:14.825 --> 1:55:17.327
[Kurtz] I went down that river once
when I was a kid.

1:55:22.582 --> 1:55:25.001
There's a place in the river,
I can't remember...

1:55:25.752 --> 1:55:30.674
Must have been a gardenia plantation
or a flower plantation at one time.

1:55:31.007 --> 1:55:33.885
It's all wild and overgrown now,

1:55:33.969 --> 1:55:36.638
but for about 5 miles,

1:55:36.721 --> 1:55:40.267
you'd think that heaven just fell
on the earth...

1:55:41.560 --> 1:55:43.562
in the form of gardenias.

1:55:59.995 --> 1:56:01.329
Have you ever considered...

1:56:03.623 --> 1:56:05.041
any real freedoms?

1:56:10.797 --> 1:56:13.717
Freedoms from the opinion
of others...

1:56:17.304 --> 1:56:19.222
even the opinions of yourself?

1:56:20.640 --> 1:56:25.896
[water dripping]

1:56:29.733 --> 1:56:32.777
[water dripping]

1:56:35.447 --> 1:56:39.034
Did they say why... Willard?

1:56:41.244 --> 1:56:45.916
Why they want to terminate my command?

1:57:01.598 --> 1:57:03.892
I was sent on a classified mission, sir.

1:57:08.104 --> 1:57:09.648
[Kurtz] It's no longer classified...

1:57:10.649 --> 1:57:11.525
is it?

1:57:18.698 --> 1:57:19.908
What did they tell you?

1:57:23.203 --> 1:57:24.496
[Willard] They told me...

1:57:25.705 --> 1:57:26.831
that you had gone...

1:57:28.416 --> 1:57:29.584
totally insane.

1:57:32.504 --> 1:57:33.630
And, uh...

1:57:34.005 --> 1:57:37.050
that your... methods were...

1:57:38.176 --> 1:57:39.052
unsound.

1:57:42.764 --> 1:57:44.599
Are my methods unsound?

1:57:50.814 --> 1:57:52.148
I don't see...

1:57:53.191 --> 1:57:54.192
any method...

1:57:56.111 --> 1:57:57.028
at all, sir.

1:58:03.910 --> 1:58:05.203
[Kurtz] I expected...

1:58:06.663 --> 1:58:07.747
someone like you.

1:58:10.917 --> 1:58:12.335
What did you expect?

1:58:20.510 --> 1:58:22.053
Are you an assassin?

1:58:27.100 --> 1:58:28.143
I'm a soldier.

1:58:32.022 --> 1:58:33.023
You're neither.

1:58:35.775 --> 1:58:37.360
You're an errand boy...

1:58:39.029 --> 1:58:40.947
sent by grocery clerks...

1:58:44.909 --> 1:58:46.286
to collect a bill.

1:58:50.081 --> 1:58:54.836
[flies buzzing]

1:59:02.969 --> 1:59:07.057
[flies buzzing]

1:59:12.562 --> 1:59:15.273
[flies buzzing]

1:59:30.664 --> 1:59:31.915
[photographer] Why, huh?

1:59:32.874 --> 1:59:34.501
Why would a nice guy like you...

1:59:35.126 --> 1:59:36.419
want to kill a genius?

1:59:43.218 --> 1:59:44.719
Feeling pretty good, huh?

1:59:45.762 --> 1:59:46.638
Why?

1:59:48.723 --> 1:59:49.641
You know.

1:59:51.101 --> 1:59:52.602
Do you know that the man...

1:59:56.481 --> 1:59:58.274
The man really likes you?

2:00:01.820 --> 2:00:03.613
He likes you. He really likes you.

2:00:03.947 --> 2:00:04.823
But...

2:00:06.366 --> 2:00:07.992
he's got something in mind for you.

2:00:09.369 --> 2:00:10.537
Aren't you curious about that?

2:00:11.579 --> 2:00:12.455
I'm curious.

2:00:13.748 --> 2:00:14.916
I'm very curious.

2:00:16.292 --> 2:00:17.210
Are you curious?

2:00:20.380 --> 2:00:22.173
There's something happening out here, man.

2:00:26.636 --> 2:00:29.097
You know something, man?
I know something that you don't know.

2:00:29.764 --> 2:00:31.015
That's right, Jack.

2:00:31.433 --> 2:00:33.601
The man is clear in his mind,

2:00:34.978 --> 2:00:36.312
but his soul is mad.

2:00:38.398 --> 2:00:39.315
Oh, yeah.

2:00:41.234 --> 2:00:42.610
He's dying, I think.

2:00:43.236 --> 2:00:45.447
He hates all this. He hates it.

2:00:46.406 --> 2:00:50.034
But the man's, uh...

2:00:53.580 --> 2:00:55.832
He reads poetry out loud, all right?

2:00:58.084 --> 2:00:59.002
And a voice...

2:01:00.962 --> 2:01:01.880
A voice...

2:01:04.924 --> 2:01:06.843
He likes you 'cause you're still alive.

2:01:08.011 --> 2:01:09.387
He's got plans for you.

2:01:09.804 --> 2:01:12.640
No, no, I'm not going to help you.

2:01:13.057 --> 2:01:14.434
You're going to help him, man.

2:01:15.477 --> 2:01:16.561
You're going to help him.

2:01:17.187 --> 2:01:19.606
I mean, what are they going to say, man,
when he's gone, huh?

2:01:19.814 --> 2:01:22.317
'Cause he dies when it dies, man.

2:01:22.484 --> 2:01:24.444
When it dies, he dies.

2:01:24.527 --> 2:01:26.738
What are they going to say about him?
What, they gonna say,

2:01:26.821 --> 2:01:30.116
"He was a kind man, he was a wise man.

2:01:30.241 --> 2:01:32.327
He had plans, he had wisdom?"

2:01:32.410 --> 2:01:33.661
Bullshit, man!

2:01:34.120 --> 2:01:37.081
Am I going to be the one
that's gonna set them straight?

2:01:37.207 --> 2:01:38.500
Look at me. Wrong.

2:01:42.212 --> 2:01:43.338
You.

2:01:48.593 --> 2:01:50.428
[Chef] Almost eight hours.

2:01:53.223 --> 2:01:54.098
God.

2:01:55.391 --> 2:01:56.559
I'm asleep.

2:01:58.561 --> 2:02:01.314
I'm asleep and dreaming
I'm on this shitty boat.

2:02:13.243 --> 2:02:14.244
Fuck.

2:02:18.623 --> 2:02:20.166
Has it been eight hours?

2:02:22.210 --> 2:02:24.629
-[radio static]
-Hello, Almighty, Almighty.

2:02:24.712 --> 2:02:27.966
-[radio static]
-This is PBR Street Gang.

2:02:28.258 --> 2:02:30.260
-Radio check, over.
-[radio static]

2:02:30.677 --> 2:02:33.304
[man over radio] PBR Street Gang,
This is Almighty standing by, over.

2:02:33.388 --> 2:02:34.347
