2:02:36.850 --> 2:02:38.476
[thunder rumbles]

2:02:54.576 --> 2:02:55.869
[thunder rumbles]

2:03:28.818 --> 2:03:35.491
[thunder rumbles]

2:03:53.301 --> 2:03:55.303
[Willard screams]

2:03:56.971 --> 2:03:59.515
Oh! Oh, Jesus!

2:04:05.939 --> 2:04:08.149
Oh, Christ!

2:04:10.360 --> 2:04:11.861
[groans]

2:05:17.552 --> 2:05:19.804
[wood creaking]

2:06:21.365 --> 2:06:22.617
[fly buzzes]

2:06:35.630 --> 2:06:37.215
[Kurtz] "We are the hollow men,

2:06:38.674 --> 2:06:40.051
we are the stuffed men,

2:06:40.593 --> 2:06:42.053
leaning together,

2:06:42.845 --> 2:06:44.472
headpiece filled with straw.

2:06:45.223 --> 2:06:46.182
Alas!

2:06:47.683 --> 2:06:50.269
Our dried voices
when we whisper together

2:06:50.394 --> 2:06:51.813
are quiet and meaningless

2:06:51.938 --> 2:06:53.439
as wind in dry grass...

2:06:54.982 --> 2:06:57.819
-or rats' feet in a dry cellar"
-[photographer] Oh, he's out there.

2:06:59.237 --> 2:07:00.613
He's really out there.

2:07:00.822 --> 2:07:02.073
[Kurtz] "Shape without form.

2:07:03.908 --> 2:07:05.326
Shade without color.

2:07:06.577 --> 2:07:08.121
Paralyzed force.

2:07:09.664 --> 2:07:11.040
Gesture without motion."

2:07:11.374 --> 2:07:13.126
[photographer]
Do you know what the man's saying?

2:07:14.335 --> 2:07:17.672
Do you? This is dialectics.

2:07:18.297 --> 2:07:20.800
It's very simple dialectics,
one through nine.

2:07:20.925 --> 2:07:23.302
No maybes, no supposes, no fractions.

2:07:23.469 --> 2:07:26.722
You can't travel in space.
You can't go out into space, you know,

2:07:26.806 --> 2:07:28.850
without, like, you know, with fractions.

2:07:28.933 --> 2:07:30.726
What are you going to land on? 1/4, 3/8?

2:07:30.810 --> 2:07:33.646
What are you going to do when you go
from here to Venus or something?

2:07:33.729 --> 2:07:35.481
That's dialectic. Physics, okay?

2:07:35.690 --> 2:07:37.608
Dialectic logic is
there's only love and hate.

2:07:37.692 --> 2:07:40.027
You either love somebody or you hate them.

2:07:40.444 --> 2:07:41.487
[Kurtz] Mutt!

2:07:43.865 --> 2:07:44.782
You mutt.

2:07:45.491 --> 2:07:48.828
This is the way the fucking world ends.

2:07:48.911 --> 2:07:50.997
Look at this fucking shit we're in, man!

2:07:51.497 --> 2:07:53.457
Not with a bang, a whimper.

2:07:53.541 --> 2:07:56.085
And with a whimper,
I'm fucking splitting, Jack.

2:08:25.823 --> 2:08:28.534
[Willard] On the river, I thought that
the minute I looked at him

2:08:28.618 --> 2:08:29.785
I'd know what to do.

2:08:31.454 --> 2:08:32.747
But it didn't happen.

2:08:34.624 --> 2:08:36.417
I was in there with him for days,

2:08:37.251 --> 2:08:38.211
not under guard.

2:08:39.086 --> 2:08:40.004
I was free.

2:08:41.255 --> 2:08:43.174
But he knew I wasn't going anywhere.

2:08:44.634 --> 2:08:47.303
He knew more about what I was
going to do than I did.

2:08:55.144 --> 2:08:58.481
If the generals back in Nha Trang
could see what I saw,

2:08:59.523 --> 2:09:01.234
would they still want me to kill him?

2:09:03.402 --> 2:09:04.904
More than ever, probably.

2:09:06.656 --> 2:09:08.699
And what would his people back home want

2:09:08.783 --> 2:09:11.577
if they ever learned just how far
from them he'd really gone?

2:09:14.413 --> 2:09:15.289
He broke from them,

2:09:16.374 --> 2:09:17.917
and then he broke from himself.

2:09:19.418 --> 2:09:21.754
I'd never seen a man so broken up and...

2:09:22.797 --> 2:09:23.798
ripped apart.

2:09:24.548 --> 2:09:25.841
[Kurtz] I've seen horrors.

2:09:27.385 --> 2:09:29.053
Horrors that you've seen.

2:09:31.389 --> 2:09:33.599
But you have no right to call me
a murderer.

2:09:33.683 --> 2:09:35.017
You have a right to kill me.

2:09:36.811 --> 2:09:38.938
You have a right to do that.

2:09:40.940 --> 2:09:42.692
But you have no right to judge me.

2:09:49.949 --> 2:09:51.909
It's impossible for words...

2:09:53.828 --> 2:09:55.204
to describe...

2:09:57.415 --> 2:10:00.251
what is... necessary...

2:10:02.670 --> 2:10:06.382
to those who do not know

2:10:07.800 --> 2:10:10.720
what horror means.

2:10:12.930 --> 2:10:13.848
Horror.

2:10:17.226 --> 2:10:19.729
Horror has a face...

2:10:22.356 --> 2:10:24.150
and you must make a friend of horror.

2:10:25.943 --> 2:10:30.781
Horror and moral terror are your friends.

2:10:31.490 --> 2:10:36.120
If they are not, then they are enemies to
be feared.

2:10:37.788 --> 2:10:39.165
They are truly enemies.

2:10:44.712 --> 2:10:47.506
I remember
when I was with Special Forces.

2:10:52.094 --> 2:10:55.931
Seems... a thousand centuries ago.

2:10:59.477 --> 2:11:05.316
We went into a camp
to inoculate... some children.

2:11:10.029 --> 2:11:11.280
We'd left the camp,

2:11:12.865 --> 2:11:15.618
after we had inoculated the children
for polio,

2:11:17.953 --> 2:11:21.499
and this old man came running after us,
and he was crying, he couldn't say.

2:11:24.919 --> 2:11:26.545
We went back there

2:11:27.296 --> 2:11:32.843
and they had come and hacked off
every inoculated arm.

2:11:35.304 --> 2:11:37.139
There they were in a pile,

2:11:37.723 --> 2:11:38.682
a pile of...

2:11:41.060 --> 2:11:41.936
little arms.

2:11:44.355 --> 2:11:46.690
And I remember...

2:11:48.651 --> 2:11:49.527
I-- I...

2:11:50.611 --> 2:11:53.155
I cried, I wept like...

2:11:55.282 --> 2:11:57.326
some... grandmother.

2:12:00.246 --> 2:12:03.582
I wanted to tear my teeth out.
I didn't know what I wanted to do.

2:12:05.292 --> 2:12:07.628
And I want to remember it,
I never want to forget it.

2:12:08.546 --> 2:12:09.922
I never want to forget.

2:12:11.966 --> 2:12:16.512
And then I realized... like I was shot,

2:12:17.096 --> 2:12:19.056
like I was shot with a diamond,

2:12:20.516 --> 2:12:23.602
a diamond bullet
right through my forehead

2:12:25.729 --> 2:12:28.774
and I thought,
"My God! The genius of that,

2:12:29.692 --> 2:12:34.697
the genius, the will to do that."

2:12:36.365 --> 2:12:41.287
Perfect, genuine, complete,
crystal and pure.

2:12:43.456 --> 2:12:49.003
Then I realized they were stronger than we
because they could stand it.

2:12:49.086 --> 2:12:53.132
These were not monsters,
these were men, trained cadres.

2:12:54.508 --> 2:12:56.927
These men fought with their hearts,

2:12:57.094 --> 2:12:59.013
who have families, who have children,

2:12:59.346 --> 2:13:00.723
who are filled with love,

2:13:01.432 --> 2:13:03.309
but they had the strength...

2:13:04.894 --> 2:13:06.228
the strength...

2:13:10.357 --> 2:13:11.484
to do that.

2:13:12.401 --> 2:13:16.864
If I had 10 divisions of those men,

2:13:17.781 --> 2:13:20.701
then our troubles here
would be over very quickly.

2:13:22.536 --> 2:13:23.787
You have to have men

2:13:26.040 --> 2:13:26.999
who are moral,

2:13:29.251 --> 2:13:30.836
and at the same time,

2:13:31.712 --> 2:13:36.592
who are able to utilize their...

2:13:39.178 --> 2:13:41.263
primordial instincts to kill,

2:13:43.098 --> 2:13:45.434
without feeling, without passion,

2:13:47.269 --> 2:13:49.813
without judgment. Without judgment.

2:13:55.152 --> 2:13:57.613
Because it's judgment that defeats us.

2:14:03.452 --> 2:14:07.206
[fly buzzing]

2:14:17.383 --> 2:14:19.009
I worry that my son

2:14:20.553 --> 2:14:24.306
might not understand what I've tried to be

2:14:26.850 --> 2:14:31.605
and if I were to be killed, Willard,

2:14:33.148 --> 2:14:38.696
I would want someone to go to my home
and tell my son everything.

2:14:41.824 --> 2:14:45.035
Everything I did, everything you saw.

2:14:46.245 --> 2:14:48.956
Because there's nothing
that I detest more than...

2:14:50.040 --> 2:14:52.084
the stench of lies.

2:14:55.170 --> 2:14:57.756
And if you understand me, Willard, you...

2:15:00.175 --> 2:15:02.052
You will do this for me.

